user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bianca Regano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXSGsO_a3Alj2aXsXTyPkv8QVhZN-FZzY8kjQYQ6tnscjEDzE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely lovely venue, the customer service was fantastic and they even noted my birthday for a little free dessert. Things like that really make an experience great. We had a steak and the pork cutlet, could not fault the food in any way. Might be the best dinner out l’ve ever had. The Sun Baker cocktail was beautiful and delicious and the ambiance was terrific. 5/5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKtNviOk3qTy_hVsfOka-tj6kFV2E0zUKw276p"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Chris Lawson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDI27xI5HVixwpikvwyjtbj3wyqH8RRblPb4AFVRsVPOjVHPI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Beautifully set out dining room and getting to look into the kitchen where the magic happens. The food was delicious the crust on the steak was perfect. The wine list is extensive but there's some gems at the right price point.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSH7-BqrfVIB3dZA11fR4B1Hzc3n2gKdMQkrc"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"shani goulter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTPczbg_mYSrz0F_GrI9P34mmnk84VEbp8odKvQWdUE5pAQw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"went here saturday night 20/04 for a yr anniversary.
The highlight was the customer service, we were served by a really lovely man, he was very friendly and bubbly, and took great care of our service. Just want to make it known his efforts don’t go unnoticed!!!
our food was well worth the money, my steak was absolutely delicious, and my partner loved his dish as well!
thanks for making our one year a memorable one 💞","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNITiowkaZcoxPuqsaUZk01j46pFd9Nx6iArm2r"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Karolis Sinkevicius","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVEIcf3gQKu69exmgTgu4nrsRX9wvbgmqUAAzZk53-G0iJ_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was one of the best meals I've had in Brisbane! I had the Angus prime steak, which was cooked to perfection. Major compliments to the kitchen, and the service was brilliant as well. I highly recommend the restaurant for anyone wanting to have a good night, great for a romantic setting too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM9l4lCc-ioRpiRHmhba_T1aYvVvdslc194kzx"],"When":"2024-5-11"},{"Name":"Greg Toomey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXD-vgrQr6rSYiq6jdBCXQVS1UyLlpjRZvZ-vI_ei5o2DuM0GLOyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow what an incredible experience! The staff were attentive and super-professional, but friendly not stiff. I can't find enough superlatives to describe the food. The best Barramundi I've ever tasted; the seafood platter was uber-fresh, and the duck-liver pate and dutch baked potatoes were to die for. Unfortunately they ran out of tomato juice so I couldn't get a Bloody Mary so had to settle for a Martini instead. The atmosphere was busy but the beautiful surroundings and river views were spectacular.
Blackbird sets the gold standard for Brisbane restaurants and I will definitely be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOz_uGfkHAKqrx5TWKjE-PTRtUTXFL3TUftBFf5"],"When":"2024-2-6"},{"Name":"Bill","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVp-LS8fTgDLaKs54cCZe3g27n2yhQcQX89Hx7E3jJDJ4vgMjHWxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had Christmas Day Lunch at Blackbird. It was a 4 course set menu with premium drinks package. Outstanding food, excellent service and brilliant view of the river while dining. Couldn't fault the day. Thank you for a lovely Christmas Lunch.

Update 26/01/2024

We had the Bar set for 4 Pax
Really good value @ $35 per person for what you get.
Seafood platter, charcuterie platter, Croquettes and a cheese platter that was to die for.
Combined with a few cocktails it was a great night.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOG8Dt_B8_PBqt18ftIaOOi1vVYu1Cxb9BHaCHG"],"When":"2023-12-25"},{"Name":"Ella Dehghanzadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWaSOP_WHOfWYaN9tul8zoKmdlzb9lqgyFOrjacQU14lDXN4x4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have nice food but the service is next level!
Such a nice helpful well trained staff.
But the environment is busy and noisy, that’s why I reckon it’s a nice place for business meetings not date nights.
Got marinated albacore tuna(fresh tasty tuna), coral coast barramundi ( nice but a bit salty for me), king river wagyu ( very well seasoned and best dish on the table), QLD baked blue pumpkin ( nice as a side to wagyu)
Also I don’t recommend ordering cocktails here because the execution is basic as you can see in photos","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOk0ErziYBoSm2h7Fjiuzrjrvh8Jq9t73alb3xl"],"When":"2024-2-22"},{"Name":"David Bertholini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIdqrT9YzUe2-zOBKd_bAEMF-vvQblHbCTjXYV3ekGOhwY8fA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s hard to pick the highlight of our night. The location and view are unbeatable. The food and drink superb. And our waiter Juan was almost a mind reader - he unobtrusively delivered great service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOn8rsnw3NdZrNWmkuevXaLoJrpCkYIt12RWAVK"],"When":"2024-6-1"}]

[{"Name":"Aakanksha K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxer98YS99hWCK9wjhkBk5s4Goh08Y2Dx-GKkr3idqADxumnDO1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Perfect place nestled right in the middle of Hilton, had a great time with my friends. The staff is professional and cocktails are well made. The lounge atmosphere is sophisticated and elegant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2aYDqNgZjLoDnW85C6q_DRQqLUn166f2U_Sv3"],"When":"2024-3-15"},{"Name":"Feasting with Zen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrsS_H571z3WQeA2OfwW7kfAY8sCH9b1hWv1hcttPvRi-eizQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"When we first arrived, we came a little earlier to take a seat in the lounge/bar area, to enjoy a drink before dinner.  I had to order our drinks twice before actually receiving our order.

We were a large table of 9 and had been offered the private dining room when making the booking.
This was a really nice opportunity to have some privacy, when dining with a large group.

At the beginning the service in the restaurant was amazing, the team where very tentative refilling our drinks and checking on the food.
However after the food was served, I felt like the staff  disappeared.

Later In the evening I went to order a drink and the staff member told me last drinks had already been called, however it must of been a whispered as no one at our table was aware.

The food was nice the service over all was ok, would I rush back probably not. It’s a shame as this place has so much potential!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6QHYJtvSV4Ncd8H_Uc_1YpqQFn8me_YXdkPuA"],"When":"2023-7-4"},{"Name":"Peta Crowe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdJxZv3oruQwobNZgnae8J-K0yNwAAb-qd0eRKOUPSr1bnQf8W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Booked an experience for a birthday dinner.
Had the 2kg Tomahawk Steak Shared Meal.
The service was impeccable, from being called the day before to confirm how we liked our steak cooked, to being seated and served, the staff were amazing.
The Tomahawk was impressive and you felt very special having it carved at the table.
If you want to feel special or treat someone special - this is the way to do it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Grahame Thompson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVStASCJcraDdDlPgI5K5h-pMMWByVpNVJXs2GD9Z3BAjE99xvG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"At the Hilton Brisbane, as you should expect, only the best will do (sounds like a slogan, I know). It is a great meeting up place to enjoy some beverages and the odd bar snack or meal. Well worth stopping by.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"D and D D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuCHxGZrAzpGwV4yiAKJ1QEAkYbSB6M4hbSkTGGz4Wm5JEhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had high tea with my family, and some bar food. The lamb ribs and chips were great! The high tea was even better! Coffee perfect. Everything perfect. Thankyou guys!!! Special shout out to our host, I think his name was Wayman!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZ7QARNjMVwFTHnJoCuVC3aT6ibYnvuezQ1PdL"],"When":"2023-10-7"},{"Name":"John Montesalvo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVE25LhXFZcl1J5QgingM4EbjjTLO82Folv0xNeiNY7AF_Jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"What a shame
Vintaged at the Hilton is a beautifully laid out restaraunt. The atmosphere is great. The service is impeccable. The duck that my partner had was plentiful and tasty and the desert she had was delicious. I decided to have the 380 day grain fed 6+ Waygu  at $125 for 300 gram. Plus, wait for it $4 for Bernadine sauce…. Seriously ?
Make a long story short this was no $125 steak + $4 sauce. Nothing wrong with it, it was just an ordinary Waygu  that you could buy at Coles, if they sold Waygu.
The week previously I had the same steak at the Regetta for $89 and that was beyond delicious.
As I say, what a shame.
Do I need to go back……..probably not.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrO9GvgfAXmRLIM4866soqHeg1Y5d6m3-VxKIG"],"When":"2022-9-24"},{"Name":"G IM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGuc06EPV66xlsko0AMiQQcNy25DssmJpO7jUbxaYKZgXR6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We made a lunch reservation and visited the restaurant. We booked at 11:30 am through the OpenTable app via their website and received a confirmation email. However, upon arrival we found out that lunch service starts at 12 pm, so we had to wait for almost an hour in the cafe area in front of the restaurant. After ordering our meal, it took 40 minutes to receive the first entrée dish. We were the first table there. Subsequently, we waited almost 30 more minutes for the main dishes. The hall staff were hard to find, and the experience did not match the hospitality expected from a 5-star hotel restaurant. We couldn't see any staff until we asked them to clear the used plates and cutlery after each course, as well as the empty drink bottles and glasses. Overall, the food was excellent, and the atmosphere of the restaurant was fine. However, the hospitality aspect was very disappointing and left us quite upset.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kylierobson collins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxVlYTIEp77wwqHOY28qIc5UqGEvJz5qLyRXVXk-bhwOj6xVgf1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"When I want a quiet, relaxing cuppa, I head to the Hilton Brisbane. The staff are friendly and warm the surroundings always makes me feel like I'm visiting an old friend.  I love it there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKlbqmsxSwK7u-T42H4Stp9rxsra1gQP3hx7ZD"],"When":"2023-10-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Molly Siu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcQigGIs05NPPL0NLQVC2SH5TlshDb5ZwGU9MMo8sJUFCbIuUf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Samantha is amazing! Super friendly and helpful 🥰food is exceptional! And love the wine list! This become my favourite yum chat in the city","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZ4xH6C_zTKo1HyOzufEk3RMw3Clxi345Yk3QF"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Vicky Zhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV3sPrAgqxZFq4SudstTtAlVEaQ7fbEoMvzWA2SLI9hIA6-gA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a Chinese restaurant specializing in Cantonese dim sum, located in Brisbane CBD. You can stop by here while shopping on weekends to eat and chat. There are many dishes to choose from, as well as a variety of alcoholic beverages. The truffle fried rice and roasted quail are particularly delicious. The service is attentive and thoughtful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxQzsDG1RFz67Wpi-HS1fWsrhyeXb0_zHqui89"],"When":"2024-4-14"},{"Name":"Sally L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8_ckBmZ9qvd1BUA5HGuLFlsyzGOaonOvGkXbjyqPGlC6HKNuI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Yum Cha restaurant in Brisbane and one of the best restaurants in Brisbane! We visited for our mum’s birthday dinner and the food, the Peking duck presentation and the service, everything was just superb. Thank you Jason for looking after us! Also, not many restaurants get both the food AND drinks right, but this place does it all! Highly recommend their cocktails, every one of them is delicious, you can’t go wrong! The truffle fried rice is also a must. Thanks again Jason for making mum’s birthday dinner so special! We’ll definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNliMRss8tQ3fG_4Xib4EiepTbyuEQXAI2hpe33"],"When":"2024-5-17"},{"Name":"Rachel Maunder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwYCJSaYjlpUdh7eSZMRFi6_62bpX0ZdfZh7x0Fl3t4ZmLmjqAXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lunch seating , recommendations for booking . Great service and attention to details. My waitress recommended the lobster 🦞 special. Rice and Asian greens 🥬. Will be back with more friends to try more dumplings 🥟. As dining alone this was a great recommendation. Inner city parking 🅿️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfRxwJgRHbKdaIeLe37gL_qDvpp9Dm_dN_MyHk"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Jessie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgHcN3WJA1pAQmbY9Bs1PfBJpg5PL2UVygJOYK321ULxBNlL-_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Longtime Yum Cha in Brisbane exceeded all our expectations! From the moment we arrived, we were welcomed with exceptional professionalism and warm hospitality.

The food at Longtime Yum Cha is simply amazing. Every dish we tried was a delightful explosion of flavors, clearly made with the finest ingredients and expert culinary skills. The dumplings were perfectly steamed, and the variety of dishes ensured there was something to satisfy every palate.

Ansol’s attentive and friendly service was the highlight of our visit. He was incredibly knowledgeable about the menu, offered fantastic recommendations. His genuine care and attention to detail made us feel special and well-cared-for throughout our meal.

The ambiance of the restaurant is warm and inviting, perfect for any occasion, whether it's a family gathering or a casual meal with friends. We left with full hearts and satisfied taste buds, already planning our next visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMI1y3MbbrLWBnpycrmUfnzK0cND5sJVFHaZLTW"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Aaron Hurley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQcccbYKu0eEhPWmnUm6E_uwgGg0Tt4XKtKeJJS6U_umKZGSvM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After having the most amazing service in Melbourne last week I was pleasantly surprised that I had even better service in this Brisbane CBD restaurant. Our waitress was so attentive and friendly (she overheard me tell my friends that I burnt my hand earlier when she was serving our drinks and she offered to get me a Band Aid). Talking about going above and beyond.
The food was also overwhelming delicious- I dined with Korean and Taiwanese friends and they said it was some of the best Asian food they’d had in Brisbane.
Highly, highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1SqUE1Ozy5nAC9ZePf92EPpJ_wy4bwlEI0D0V"],"When":"2024-3-24"},{"Name":"roshan adhikari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpTnPV2wW6qtJpvteN1kvn3iDzE5YBUwL2_emHGg9Csndcpa7n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Been here few times.
Good food but the only problem is they serve everything at same time. If i spend $100 per person i need some time( as i said to waiter to bring slow). The beef stir fry was not the best i had for the price. Not really worth trying. Everything else is good. 😌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJ1JZmp09mTEk7f5hQdyq_P0nUcBjK-Q_8FBVV"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Lisa “Food Digger” C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPHhUm7gMon0AQMyZt6pQ4LeoKdrNXiTcHb_DDh9jyYqkwmDwF8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice Cantonese place in the heart of Brisbane.
Staff were very welcoming and checked on us a lot. Decor is very nice and comfortable.
Great for large tables.
Been a while since I had Yum Cha for dinner. Anytime is good for dim sums if they are made well 👍🏻
As you can see we tried a few things.
Highly recommend the Char Kway Diu, Prawn Dumplings, Duck, Fried Prawn Rolls, Truffle Fried Rice and Radish Cake.
There is Parking inside the shopping centre.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFyw7YKkowR-h87uQe_5Egs284XHa13y8ux5Mc"],"When":"2024-5-2"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Taras Dranik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXo4GgMqk5REMoUEEhoHVdZxi-462A1q7u61RgX0ZpGNc-ehcY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Dried fried chicken was a delightful surprise. It had a great taste with just the right amount of spice. Definitely a highlight!

Unfortunately, the double cooked pork was only average. The portion size was also quite small.

The restaurant's floor is very slippery. One of the staff members even fell down, but thankfully, it wasn't anything major.

While the experience was good, there was nothing particularly special about this restaurant. It's worth a visit for the chicken, but they need to address the slippery floor situation. 🥡","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1OXAGglxGOQYbJohZByxJ3oGog42KoI7DwGrb"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"Tamia Song","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMPVcC52cATidm2sh7Z8co-7MtJ6lnK7pgpj0Rjd9resREbg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love their beef on the hot stone. It's my must-have. Tried the fish for the first time and it was tender and juicy - really nice! Very spicy tho. Ma-po tofu was good, too. It's a shame the bean jelly noodles weren't available. There's only one staff at lunch time. Hard to get help sometimes. The beef on hot stones used to be served differently - puring the hot oil on the meat and have that sizzling in front of you. Wasn't given the piece of bread to soak up the oil initially. Had to ask for it. Didn't like the rice either - taste like leftover rice. But overall still good experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMETxHc7qUI7cvZ8qnpHd-eq_7seRL6cbyFVbVZ"],"When":"2024-1-17"},{"Name":"Winston Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYGhjmQyUy907XrJsbbnbmyvWsUyP1zj3cfSN3mDxDFaduQIFc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Been here 3 times. Mostly enjoyable Sichuan food - high in both flavour and price.

The restaurant is centrally located at the base of The Westin Brisbane on Mary St in the CBD, and offers a range of indoor and outdoor seating, plus some private function rooms if that’s more your style. The menu is extensive, with a focus on Sichuan items. But if you’re like my family who can’t handle much heat, there are non-spicy options too.

Items I've tried over 3 visits are listed below. Favourites are marked with a 👍

First visit April 2022
* deep fried shallot pancake 蔥油餅, $6
* 👍 tea smoked duck with pancakes and sweet bean sauce 一品樟茶鴨, $42
* boiled assorted vegetables in rice soup 米湯耙耙菜, $19
* rice, $3/person

Second visit October 2022
* Braised ox tongue, $39 - with Chinese cabbage, black fungus, green Sichuan peppercorn oil, and sesame oil. We were actually after the sliced ox tongue ($24) and thought that's what we ordered  but didn't realise there were 2 ox tongue items and a little miscommunication resulted in us getting a different dish!
* 👍Spicy lamb ribs, $36 - with capsicum, onions, peanuts, coriander, cumin, and paprika
* 👍"yu xiang" eggplant, $23 - with pork mince in sweet sour sauce
Our party also had some drinks (lychee punch $8, watermelon punch $6, watermelon juice $8)

Third visit July 2023
* Tofu pudding, $31 - with salted egg yolk, fish roe and crab meat. The dish presented differently to the menu though - had to look very closely to spot the crab 😅
* Double cooked pork, $31
* 👍Stir fried green beans, $24","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS4ICZyhWUCPsgBWsG8lHgjFdljJsv-EYZgWPa"],"When":"2023-7-5"},{"Name":"dear friend,","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgKI-qnnS5DpQaUkQ7I3yVbd6MQxSaDpkOajcKx6LUHODLlfU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best kaoyu ever!!!!!!!! If you like spicy food pleeeeeaz try it. It was the best food ive ever eaten in brisbane. I wish i could eat again..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZoiVDugxuByc65BRPmyU7I3rWLu4lJkJD8SjZ"],"When":"2024-4-26"},{"Name":"Cindy Yap","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU2mJqfqxFeutjHLYq6R1tuJe5VRY3VSHPIRFgsvMVk0ahpApc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The staff are not well trained as they have no idea what they are doing.

The restaurant floor is very greasy and oily is absolutely disgusting. It was hard to walk on the tiles floor. I never seen any restaurant like this.

Our table was very greasy and definitely they clean it but not properly ….

I tried many Sichuan but this is the worst Sichuan restaurant in Australia so far…

Tiny piece of pork mince with eggplant or maybe not even a pork inside the dish. Not worth it at all. I wouldn’t recommend this place and ever go back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNP-XzROJRPTT8TQLEpSciVGxS35YhHYuoB33Qs"],"When":"2024-4-5"},{"Name":"eugenetytan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvzj1NbDoLp5ftr5U85xYPgfYjeCsDo1wrze9QwLhTmUMRuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great Chinese food in heart of Brisbane.  One of the better Chinese restaurants you can find in the area.  The fish was fresh, and the long beans was one of the best I’ve had in Brisbane.  The lamb ribs was a little over cooked and dry to my liking.  Overall, still good Chinese food at reasonable pricing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeHGhQfGxRVZAh5RlFDttmgmI01zGLHhp9z4ij"],"When":"2023-6-5"},{"Name":"Lawrence","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIIf5inMNTvj_xNsrHTgqRywpuK8Hf6p0VefvgtrV_JqAOb2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered 4 mains and 1 entree
- steam chicken with chili oil: it’s different with what you order from other sichuan restaurant. But it tastes really good, like the peanut and celery combination.
- braised black mullet: nice and authentic.
- braised ox tongue: nice and recommended.
- deep fried chicken: they use boneless chicken for this dish, taste great.
- fried green bean: taste nice.
Food is good, but the customer service needs to be improved. There is a skinny guy with glasses, he needs to learn how to serve customer. He is so rude!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOteVESgE1P4LIUmFAhl7rqtaGVYnEeiPilCjMG"],"When":"2022-11-20"},{"Name":"Nancy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9JX7bc86Y_ZmP38ewsyVIKBGYKYncBpFG92qZw9hK7rXh5C4n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Well presented restaurant serving authentic Chinese cuisine located next to the Westin Hotel in Brisbane CBD. They do offer a wide selection of dishes ranging from the super spicy black mullet braised in chilli oil and peppercorn to non-spicy tea-smoked duck. There’s something for every taste bud. The dishes are not small in portion and are mostly designed to be shared so its ideal to dine in a group of 3-4 if you’d like to try a few dishes. Or just be prepared to take some leftovers home (like we always do) as their food still taste delicious after reheating.

The two of us ordered these 3 dishes with rice and took home the leftovers which were enough for a second meal.

Dry Fried Pork intestine with dry chilli and chips - Loved the chilli infused flavour and crunchiness of all the ingredients: pork intestine, capsicum, potato, peanuts, onion. The flavour is spicy but not over the top numbing kind of spicy. The strong flavour makes it a great dish to pair with rice.

“Xu Xiang” Eggplant with pork mince and sweet sour sauce - Eggplants are cooked through and nice and soft. Sauce was delicious. If you are someone who likes eggplant in sauce, this is another flavoursome dish to pair with rice.

Spicy lamb ribs with capsicum, onions, peanuts, coriander, cumin and paprika - Amazing aroma and flavour. The lamb ribs were simply a delight and cooked to perfection. This dish is perfect to enjoy on its own or pair with rice.

They also served a small plate of picked cabbage as complimentary appetiser, which was really nice. Overall the dining experience was enjoyable. Staff were attentive although we sat at the outdoor dining area. Prices are on the expensive side. Highly recommend using Liven to buy Foodollars to get discount if you can.

Other photos feature dishes from a previous visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPybdTMprTn7seyk0pSTVI3YOCLNkQHLQG7Ab2r"],"When":"2022-11-19"}]

When ordering my cup I asked about the blends they produce and a bit rude barista said, this is the only blend we had served for so many years and that’s what you’ll get. Impeccable. Worth travelling from NZ for! Cabinet food looked beaut. Didn't realise there was also a food menu, but I wasn't exactly looking very hard to be fair. Awesome location if you like people-watching.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lewis J. Oatley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6ONy0CLDMbmXKVNKkyeV9bAOPVbINR1FXRq5j-K7oGFg6tQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Probably the best espresso I had during my short trip to Sydney but what topped this experience was the service. The guy in the cap was most accommodating of our obnoxiously large group of friends trying to breakfast at a place clearly designed for more intimate groupings. This place gets busy but the service is quick so the wait won't be so long. The gluten free bread is great as is the wild berry jam. Menu options are Australia standard - granola and yog, chia bowl, things on toast, buddha/poke/soul bowl thing. Flat white was a little weak to my taste but I'm discovering that asking for a double shot or 'strong' flat white is necessary in Australia to get something strong and smooth, otherwise you'll have a latte in a smaller cup.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiTWveuOaBhEVNvt82IXQwIk43ppbVY4QsQ6Hf"],"When":"2019-5-8"},{"Name":"Clare Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSH-fQC8dPe1P--Y83zPzuQYnVRVGEo2KeaIU2Ggn11aOGKcfr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A great coffee place in the heart of the city, it feels more like cafe in Alexandria. Love their friendly staffs and also yummy toastie and coffee.\nJust a personal preference that I prefer more mushroom and less cheese in my toast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJN1Bzs0KKdGnpZzWmvcrZEeXNeKUaY4_gXf-0"],"When":"2018-3-14"}]

[{"Name":"hyera lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-uxv77aofOvijadDelnNRSW_zTFg55f7u0F2E06FfnF3eb8pQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My final visit to my favourite coffee place!!! I absolutely loved the way the cafe’s specific cup designs gave its infamous coffee an extra kick and vibe on to it.
I really enjoyed the meal along with the coffee and will definitely visit again with my husband next time- highly recommended
The only hope I can express here is that I wish the opening is a little longer or can be stretched to weekend so I can have my date here on my non working day pls!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4RXZ-rGl6MkiaeG5U5zVDKPCEAaRTIjTHFDbf"],"When":"2024-4-26"},{"Name":"Moira Woods","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWs5E_W8LrsYCXXik-KhjIhLv4OUI2GyVl6rHzBx3OtMvxWf1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A delicious breakfast at this busy cafe. Lovely friendly vibrant atmosphere. Our order was delivered with a smile and in very good time. Excellent coffee. A quick visit for us to Sydney but we will be back to this cafe again. Highly recommend. 😊🙏","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTpsrq4Qbp7au71lQwdcyhbnKNP0OePfjr8iVmBZDQWualC9XH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I ordered a skim iced latte. It wasn’t too bad but I thought it wasn’t as good as other places I’ve tried but still decent. The cafe had a nice atmosphere and good pastries and service was great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyRoKGsBAD3tecrkP_rWTUP_INESIhS4XLG5Zv"],"When":"2024-3-13"},{"Name":"Sansho A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYoCRk-dBe0op7ft3rVMTMOp2T7aGt_rCdNyE3fa0Zn5XmzIeX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food and chai. Had the smoked salmon bruschetta and the tomato bruschetta. Both were great. Service was attentive and friendly","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyFu9CCSDAfGq_OgwFIQsNgJSe_zI9veDeWbFV"],"When":"2024-2-18"},{"Name":"Gary Armstrong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIRwamO7xqcyzYzVCmEaOq5cUdS32OE393keqPLv2-lXUn4yyEzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely food atmosphere and staff.

Lunch menu is simple and limited for me but I think that allows the food to be made well and quickly. I had the chicken sandwich and the ingredients were quality, chicken was tender, brioche buns were toasted and buttery and the sauce was just right

I sampled the coffee flight. It's nice there's some information on the individual servings and the drinks were made with care. I'm a simple flat white enthusiast, but the expresso and filter coffee was a standout. The trailblazer coffee was a bit too milky and safe/boring but coffee is a personal preference. None of the drinks were bad and I enjoyed it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO26XrEO5uRD8xa5DMU0kYV0aUbrRKiJs9shdBW"],"When":"2023-7-18"},{"Name":"Fi Shep","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWllWARUheb1mNP2kPk4rz6vA4MQdItfEUxvrYKcZBzeBsMtvY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an absolute delight to come across this rustic cafe nestled on the corner of a building along Castlereagh St in the CBD. Access through the doors is easily via a flat slightly raised entrance. There’s a selection of tables with chairs, window bench seats and communal tables, both with high stools. The first thing I felt was how friendly the staff were, the food choices were simple and when my steak sandwich came out it was so tasty! The window bench seats are a perfect place to sit out of the way and people watch. It’s a busy cafe but people seem to move through quickly and the food (I ordered via the app which charges the extra .35 cents) came out so fast! I’ll definitely be returning again and want to try a coffee next time ☺️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLrQOAzVEQ43n7SKhpi_10iw23YbD2CZjukY1N"],"When":"2023-6-7"},{"Name":"Claire Dwyer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz8EK4tXagcVQLz1wI1ozqXZdd69TZyWWFh3v1kB9Lp2YTmj5H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great cafe in the centre of Sydney. Order via qr code and your food and drinks are brought out swiftly by the friendly staff. Enjoyed the iced mocha and brekky burger, both hitting the spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh1mDmSNeIOixL2rlsnJPQvA0_phJak76r3jCR"],"When":"2023-12-20"},{"Name":"by aninflorentia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXstMbLbWn05QWKszM0c2h3WJb3FqBRk4zR2RxkM4Dit51hU5ct=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing coffee place in the CBD! Love the industrial style and warm ambiance, even sitting outside is warm during this winter day.

Great ☕️ as always... Today I was introduced to the Porter St. blend, had it as a flatwhite, and it easily became my new favorite.

Very friendly and welcoming staffs...
Highly recommend for coffee goers to capture the real Pablo&Rusty's coffee experience. Will be back to try the brunch menu for sure! 🤍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTCV0fh8RD9LaGansC4gYC67ez81jSWZ8TMzII"],"When":"2023-7-12"}]

[{"Name":"Anthony Turner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhvt87LqRHNffCzJx9Vqp-AmTuNpALBH3H8mtQMkAl-HlDN70=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dining at Cafe Sydney was an absolute delight! From the moment we arrived, the service was impeccable—attentive, friendly, and efficient. The highlight of our meal was definitely the salmon, which was hands-down the best I’ve ever had; it was perfectly cooked and flavored to perfection. The drinks menu was equally impressive, offering a superb selection that complemented our meal beautifully. And the view? Simply stunning, providing a breathtaking backdrop that greatly enhanced our group’s dining experience. Highly recommend for anyone looking for top-notch food and service with a view that’s second to none!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwDbPnSHvO59vRb1vxmLXEM9P7j9RBIhNjVv4"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Sarah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiLQ6Up4h1syBDS4VyFqS_96GdXn1GKuX8cdJ1wvRylkllq8iL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The ambience was really nice and service was good. Only let down was the long wait time and small portions for food. Some items on the menu were sold out which was disappointing. The food was average-good, nothing was a standout. We were moved to another area at around 4:30 for them to prepare for the dinner service, however it was odd because they let other people stay in the dining or move outdoors. I would recommend coming here for a drink, they’re made really well and during sunset!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLDWIqe93Ikk_vapV4VxEgmaz8qDo-32Hd9XCb"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"M C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLd7zWjcv0S6Q8_7kK5VnL2fiXAxCKY_vjV-dvF6KVJS68dsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My recent visit to Cafe Sydney was nothing short of spectacular. Nestled near Circular Quay, the restaurant offers breathtaking views of the Harbour Bridge and Opera House, perfectly complementing its outstanding service and culinary delights.

The menu impressed with a variety of options catering to diverse tastes. I opted for the Barramundi, beautifully presented and incredibly fresh. My husband savored the Berkshire Pork Belly, juicy and succulent, showcasing the chef's expertise. Additionally, the Octopus I ordered was divine, cooked to perfection and bursting with flavor.

Not to be overlooked, the dessert was a highlight of our dining experience. The Hazelnut dessert paired with ice cream was an absolute delight, offering a sublime ending to our meal. Our friend enjoyed the Lamb Cutlet, which was equally praised for its flavors and preparation.

We were also pleasantly surprised by the thoughtful kids' meal options. It's rare to find  that caters so effectively to children without compromising on quality. Even the Fish and Chips from the kids' menu proved to be an excellent choice, showcasing their commitment to excellence across all dishes.

While my photos may not capture the full splendor of our meals, I cannot recommend Cafe Sydney enough. Whether you're a local or a visitor, make sure to add this gem to your Sydney itinerary for an unforgettable dining experience that combines the best of Australian cuisine with iconic views.

Rating: 5/5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_qIC7vwdQ-p7tplm-B3Ur4KTQ51yPN0fnZq43"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Daniela Fistac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXU-oUsOtR1O6-DnyEjOgGQsbh5ziWYAXD0EiWGVbhbQk6rMuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great location with Sydney view, staff very professional and friendly and the food is outstanding! Love the deserts, as in for lunch I strongly recommend the swordfish grilled which is perfectly cooked (like medium) , the most delicious fish I have ever had BUT when I visited on the following day week since my first visit they have changed the swordfish grilled and added some very bad and extremely spicy sauce, such a shame, I was very disappointed and never returned here since then.
I have attached pictures, the one that has the orange colour sauce was the great one I had
was called in the menu “Grilled swordfish, braised pepperonata squid , red capsicum sauce” and the one that has ravioli is the one bery spicy with separate sauce. The waitress was nice to warn me in advance to take the sauce separately","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOX0BinZ1sGIkM2MI737GT9aJ_BcDB5kUarKCSz"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Blake Skjellerup","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZmdpPgnaC329_UKZibjmgzoHXqJ3tbxKoqanMXxQe8xVvt6dh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Great location, sitting on the patio is a must! Wouldn't say it's worthwhile sitting anywhere else as the food is good, but doesn't match up to the stunning location looking over Circular Quay and the Harbour Bridge. We were there during Vivid and it was a great view point to sit and watch the Harbour and surroundings light up.

Service was F- grade, constantly changing waiters, slow to take orders, top up drinks, and staff weren't knowledgeable on the menu or wine list. Pretty disappointing really as it could have been a very memorable dining experience if the service was up to par.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7lS4HhfzdWGs1FeMsI9wRxjQJaQGwNpi04GW3"],"When":"2024-5-31"},{"Name":"Atez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnALI8qYFKxI9KVeobdwUFaTDZcutzKgHH1hJDfzKYIv3VCCzZAQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cafe Sydney's location overlooking the Harbour Bridge is unbeatable, especially from the patio area. They offer a good drink selection, and service is solid. However, the food is just average. If you prioritize ambiance and drinks over food quality, this spot might still be worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfNxnxfmJ1yLHnbWLKD49d0SgNIc5iB7uI0R1n"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Catharine Dunn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4rRfMmE-7GlDBPXOhNzxrLXIbL9Ile14vz4tbwiTbpn6CKg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our service attendant Ben is a true professional with charismatic personality and the food is well presented. I loved every choice especially the sauces aa I can say if I am allow to wipe the sauce clean on my plate I would.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiW9CYWAf2ledvr4_94-YLCXd45wz1bW9CH4Xd"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"R Carter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpltRE6yKr8n0OOwivt7e14qTTbBRZNF3Dtx__n3ai-SJaiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an excellent lunch at Cafe Sydney and what has compelled me to write a review was the excellent service. Every single person we encountered was attentive, gracious, and kind. They went above and beyond for my mom's 70th birthday lunch and we are so appreciative. It was incredibly busy and they made it all seem effortless. On top of that the food is absolutely delicious and the view is incredible.

Thank you especially to the gentleman who ensured we had extra room around our table to accommodate our baby (we didn't even ask) and for making my mother feel so special.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9hxDuJVNUiV8F4w1QjoudtB6NefvUOH-AACqd"],"When":"2024-4-20"}]

[{"Name":"Adriano Di Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRSi2EWAHBrfYqvz6YZOE0qQg2Z3VHZ64vP12bYdUO5-gDLM74=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Grounds of The City, located in the heart of Sydney’s CBD, offers a charming dining experience with its vintage, elegant decor, featuring recycled timber, antique fixtures, and even resident shoe-shiners. The atmosphere is reminiscent of a bygone era, creating a unique and opulent setting perfect for a memorable meal.

I had the steak baguette, which was a very tasty but needed far more seasoning. The homely cakes and homemade delights on the menu also looked inviting, making it more than just a cafe. However, the service was a tad tardy, and the staff behind the counter didn’t engage with customers at the bar seating area, which was a bit disappointing. When they came to clear my plate - no offer if I’d like a coffee or a cake, just the bill.

Overall, The Grounds of The City is a delightful spot with nice food and a captivating ambiance, though a bit more attention to service would enhance the experience. Don't forget to bring a camera to capture the beautifully crafted setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0FwhCdaZEbfYaWrkV67G67sL8u87SRSSZkfor"],"When":"2024-6-2"},{"Name":"Ermi Mendoza-Isais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBYHtH4vF7Ixsos42-v8JxklU-xuFWb9aQN0OGn5O9forIv5Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Walk into a warm and cosy retro atmosphere. The lights are dimly lit and invite you in. Retro music is playing and the wait staff from the front door to bar and table service are impeccably professional and friendly.

Good coffee and flavoursome breakfast. If you’re lactose intolerant, they don’t offer lactose free milk for your coffee.

Will come here again to try the lunch and dinner menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJkfzhNEKzRMHZDiA-zrku--m9uvGHwjESbbvq"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Trang Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVF5No_UHwFa_FBxxv9mpEQBNaVMKMBAh-MPRHsgjbO-JIyhatv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Booking a table through their system is quite easy. However we were running late on that day and gave them a call ahead of time and they were okay with it.
Ordered a few dishes to share between the four of us. Service was slow as there weren’t many waiting staff for weekend peak hours which is a shame. Nice view and vibe inside the restaurant.
Food wise is okay but nothing really stands out for me, the exception would be grilled zucchini flowers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGnW8z9D3k2qq49YFju9nr2WXbH-0gjqrJaA4z"],"When":"2024-4-25"},{"Name":"Rhiannon Lewoshko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7af6hv3_qyVaxKAZqWF1RoZQhwqsPd2IPf5BFsNl_hnIG855q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a fun coffee house in Sydney! The atmosphere of the location is amazing! Definitely feels like you’ve been taken back to a 1920’s library. Servers were very attentive and good came out pretty quickly. Prices are a bit high but this can be expected considering the presentation and freshness of the food. Would definitely revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfTjKEHz2bY7Hb-SDcUfxg0Rep-NBFwL-UP-lm"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"slavica V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKSIzpH9UbT0DCsve0ZmiAkT7PBXdnQoybybUz0m5h3r3lJg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came into the city specifically for this place.  It was extremely busy with a line out the door for lunch. The lovely man I didn't grab his name he was at the reservation booth taking customer bookings asked me to wait a moment then managed to get my son and myself a seat outside . The service was first class ....our waitress Mina was just a sweety,  very attentive.  She was serving a large area but did it with such professionalism and charm. She's the reason I'm writing this review....very impressive young lady . Food was delicious and cocktails were divine.  Dessert was just fantastic,  superb,  delectable, atmosphere was so cool. I highly recommend this place and Mina you are just excellent 👌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoBrNSXhMI04G7Skc59F6uZNZcPlsxzbvCv_UK"],"When":"2024-4-19"},{"Name":"Nerine Cummins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUk-b1uogwQliv1EWoSwjOWJpCAKPyZK3wXqct79x5JEcYjrBrU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came here because I was such a fan of the Grounds of Alexandria so I was quite excited to try this place out. I had a lovely experience with the food was very nice and the service was great, the staff were very helpful and willing to answer my questions respectfully and a quick smile. It’s in an ideal location in the CBD. I would recommend making a reservation as it can be quite busy. The prices I feel are a little high.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPAYJh0aHkeAfAsKaaJ_RfBEhtD8ubOh9B17_g"],"When":"2024-3-27"},{"Name":"Jonathan Dearing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGMnpPcPDYOnqe8iz354-qSTxCKORkTq5hQyryaHZX1vHeljSp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I really wanted to like this place more and rate it higher because it’s got a lot going for it. The look and vibe is cool, the staff are welcoming it’s a great city central location. However my avocado on toast was just meh, bread was cold and hard and the whole thing just lacked flavour, was pretty soggy in the middle too. Coffee was good and I’d go again and try something different because it’s a nice venue.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMprzYXQj9oTN0WznZqOo2ZSkYfqCofT1gMFziR"],"When":"2024-1-6"},{"Name":"Flora Collins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6GIwRX488BCL5fTRdaKjkrX-cMgcVF2aBKVz_1z2HpUfX7RkQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has an amazing vibe. Coffee was really good but I would have liked it slightly hotter (I think it’s just my personal preference, it was a cold day). The smoked trout omelette with the capers in the little jar looked and tasted beautiful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjv0A8vlp1l0L1ivAwph3Djba1RVWDRZct4oaK"],"When":"2024-6-11"}]

[{"Name":"Kieran Manning","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUW0o-21Z-QVPm2Reh8V2GoIgp6BbZhhP7mwSfBI8fN_e-D5eo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exceptional Speciality Coffee in the heart of the city. Fantastic service and highly skilled barista. Do recommend for any speciality coffee geeks reading this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEVSn6M0ROgNeh3vBxuTDMKr1MGt7PVRfMyxL2"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Ben Law","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzXX7HFIIotQWPb56As1D0hoYUZ3QGyRTt7Rz-wp1wBvFNYGwE3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great coffee, good snacks.   Highly recommend as they know their stuff here.  What you want from a Speciality Coffee Cafe","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6R_SrY_MZ0bCcGxxuvTqHUdmTIU7N8-XxpH18"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"Viana Octabella","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWS9jQl3FqcyDawjehOIo0VpMNf269z5xX9dRImxU1JjAjxWoY0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a good coffee from Skittle Lane, it was small shop but the ambience was so cozy. Surely I had to going back again. I ordered Flat White and it was one of the best i’ve ever tried.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTZEa1ttIAHKtU_6zZtKLv11JS1aOoGCtRspbr"],"When":"2023-12-12"},{"Name":"Jin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUv7TvNrjaH90WIlw8DPKlw3xMHZMZxKJoYbMwQhctWxQ-ZC0Av=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The coffee is delicious, and the ambiance is great. However, the only downside is that there are no separate tables, only staircase-style seating with chairs. It might be challenging to recommend for groups since it's not easy for several people to sit together and enjoy their meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_vLmK4Jp-OU1RE6WHPQZzw1j_EYbJw09sMUWh"],"When":"2023-7-22"},{"Name":"Nutt Choksirikulchai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlUZ2nKlu81HIGhSdhCB7C4CSjUx9wo-scM-s8ssHkjB6dkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Serious about coffee? This is the place for you! Single origin coffee beans roast to your preference, espresso or filter.
You can have black or white coffee, slow bar or speed bar, pick your choice and you won't  regret any of them! Lots of people during lunch time but the waiting time is very short. Great barista both in knowledge of coffee and barista skill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMr6gew6ZnUNMJwaycuhsLDXgJQ8ad163SjvdLV"],"When":"2023-11-13"},{"Name":"Randy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpBzB5mI0gSMErSbx1qCuB4-5Lsv332ewg8H7CkEuHqR-5Pu73=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Skittle lane sydney. Equip with la marzocco linea PB, mahlkonig e80, ek43. Coffee roaster under the same name. Busy in the morning to serve office employee. I had great coffee in here. Located at the heart of cbd.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNv7_CCAyYdvtezsdWBHKOi1BxT9HqYuJ8jcDjG"],"When":"2023-11-15"},{"Name":"Amy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU85qj_leLJtEeA1Uv8EAewbGpwcdnqqmkPtzkcOz--nURVnupP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good service. Pretty good coffee but not the best.

Cinnamon scroll was very average (dry) and the toasted croissant was OK (using a flat iron really takes away the delicious flakiness though).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWdGX2FdqHgs1Klec2bRgLxPL2fv_KH4-AELbn"],"When":"2023-10-12"},{"Name":"Laura N.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6haCzoh22jMZKuDdQMToxiacLifdvA-GQtHsqk7SZWyON9c82=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I loved their flat white. Delicious!
The coffee shop had a minimalistic, rustic style but perfect for a quick stop and to grab a sweet snack.
Very friendly baristas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHhb7Vt53R3-x-bdYIBq_TFHYvX9DgJFyEHjuH"],"When":"2023-10-16"}]

[{"Name":"Roha Asad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3xIJWPMhRufwImnXSfIQJ2zSv6UBJO7C3h66OXdC0B6e0kPo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Visited this cafe on a Saturday around 2:35PM, the closing timing on the map is 4PM but they closed their kitchen at 2:30PM saying that they can’t serve any food.
That was very disappointing. Anyways we just ordered iced coffee then as it was a hot day, the coffee tasted okay. Wouldn’t say very nice but not bad either.
They definitely need to improve their customer service a lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQOzZPHHo9HBpcyVWA9bTbt2nk9gaD_umB4jYz"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Joel Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3s63xGxsU76CwVxDH9bGt9XrpcP7fTc27pBSn1FXMhHMMEw53xw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great value big brekky at $19.90! [{"Name":"Li Chin Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyaI6fsEbi6kqTQ9s_tWrn8sb1-ZM0fgRtwdFcCxUuR3_SqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love the neatness, cleanliness and tidiness. Friendly staff leads to great service. Surprisingly soft and chewy sourdough! Vegemite spread whilst wasn't much, they gave extra butter and that's enough 😁 Pricing wise; coffee with extra shot $4.50+$0.60. 2 slices of sourdough with Vegemite n butter $6.00 (+1 extra butter). On the pricey end of the scale but that's Sydney for you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPnTlTJ_qmgoBefFnO8SLrcjR_tsI4wSz9Y3pA"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Sid Rev","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZQxifvvjUJN2uq4Tm2D5WCGgP-e_47oj8nY2wSPwqPY0ljEUs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Maybe it was 10 degrees out, and they keep their door opened in winter. Sitting down there's constant cold draft coming through and wasn't comfortable.

There's main sitting area and additional tables in the hallway of the building entry. Maybe because not many cafes open on Sundays, this cafe was packed and there was line forming outside.

Foods were okay. The takeout menu items that looked good are not available on the dining in menu unfortunately. Please consider charge more and offer them for dine in customers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM-f9cHPIMk6tFGl17EUpaLeh8pEkrQC1QOLVA"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Darren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvm7I8OFs8G44HVqZHPQwkoUBiB0EnedFQESCXZaTGC_lzsZEmjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great little Cafe in the heart of Sydney. I was staying at the Hilton Hotel and this Cafe is a very short stroll away. Service is excellent as is the speed of service which in no way detracts from the quality of the food. I enjoyed an iced latte (cold and great flavour) and the omelette which was delicious yet light. My only disappointment was that I was looking forward to trying the pancakes however they were unavailable on the day.  Definitely worth a try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPB2GfuQRTl70a23v9o8Y8sUiz6Q3GqT8Pv0Bhg"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Bazz K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6y9ug8KkPWehpWLhJQUIdCgqMauT5bCNLKFcFJYAS4P-qCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service, friendly and attentive staff.
We were a group of 9 - turnaround time for coffee and food was efficient.
Location and atmosphere was great!
Food it self - very well presented, tasty all around and portions were just perfect!
Would highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAejxKGTqAt7oK-lUANWwguWDf8hJdyu9cVUyZ"],"When":"2024-4-30"},{"Name":"Michael Case","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXq9u5zaS9wPcqzCPH19uPfbmCK6vdoZVvIDTeuzE0elFSagbM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Convenient central location. Bought take away coffee here twice. Very popular and busy cafe. Quick and friendly service. Good cappuccino. Loyalty card with the tenth coffee free. Other family members had lunch here and really enjoyed their meals.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSK44cfkEn6cvPFHZPrmFNZaOjDR7jSrCcHYQr"],"When":"2024-5-6"},{"Name":"D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWD_DxytIzGJQMznkU2WdJG_W17DQRr9_t0x25l4OJC4Oazoso=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Corn fritters are perfect.
Mango chicken salad special was a very well balanced and thought out dish.

Coffee was good, and the house made hibiscus lemonade was sweet and refreshing.

I would happily come back if I was in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsdeG6iEfRCwXKyWRFQqVCmOLDLJyVHNzRACbR"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"katherine so","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzggOTFnYi6xrG5akS9fRTFwJRXeRumJFAKwr3VYYVbG-mVw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We had been waiting for our food for more than one hours until it comes. The Salmon fillet poke bowl tastes fishy and rice is uncooked. Big breakfast- Sour dough was burnt, sausage not cooked, raw. The staff there told us that if we want a well done sausage we should told them early. 😤 But isn’t a sausage suppose to be cooked well-done?? Prawn Pasta- oily, only 6 small prawns, a bit sour. I will never recommend and come again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlXazj86sAhUspj9SHeUunvPMx7uG2IFBxRnlq"],"When":"2024-2-26"},{"Name":"Danica Sivac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-rpgVm0aNxVx8fV-MeziLU2B-DdxG_qBSm425Y-qTHhCNhg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Me and my partner went there this morning, seeing all the positive reviews we were convinced that the food would be great! , as we sat down it was a nice atmosphere , we proceeded to order the big breakfast, my partner had a hot chocolate on the side , the hot chocolate was served first and it had no flavour what so ever it was like water… wasn’t a big deal until we saw our meals , the first thing that caught our eyes was the amount of Oil on our plates!! The chicken sausages had no flavour and weren’t well cooked , the eggs looked deep fried with the amount of oil on them , nothing had flavour, side note the seats we sat on in the hall way were not comfortable at all I really don’t recommend consuming such oily food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7piZlMfiI_tkoopcjl_9jjeJSDYPrUl9-bdtk"],"When":"2024-6-11"}]

[{"Name":"E Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLP_KLgNO1BP43fkheMr_kGZ0bR2vCaGL8eSQyeZVRRa8QhPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Wow, where do I start. Came here for breakfast with my wife during our stay in Sydney after reading generally positive reviews and it's an understatement to say we came away very disappointed and ripped off. We ordered the French toast and the "special" vanilla porridge together with two long black coffees.

Coffee was one of the worst coffees I've ever tried. I make coffee at home myself and my coffee tastes a thousand times better than what we were given. It had so much astringent taste, it was disgusting. Do you guys actually taste what you are making?

The special vanilla porridge is a downright rip off. If you are going to call it a special and charge 17 dollars for it, you really need to make it special. Instead it was just a cheap rolled oat you can buy at woolies for $1.40 for 750g bag cooked in milk with tiny amount of fruit on top. 17 dollars for that? You've got to be kidding me. See the photo for yourself and decide for yourself whether that's worth 17 dollars.

French toast was slightly better but nothing to write home about either. The bread tasted average at best.

Lastly, charging customers 30 cents plus 1.9% order fee for the inconvenience of having to order food through their website is a joke. You have to even put in your personal details like name, phone number and email address to be able to put in the order. So you are charging customers for doing the job your employees should be doing? On top of that, Google pay option doesn't even work for some reason so we were forced to use the credit card option which once again comes with additional fees on top.

If you are reading this, I would steer well clear from this establishment. There are tons of better options out there. Should have just gone to Joe Black Coffee where we had fabulous breakfast a few days ago.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRtUAt1AhvpjlzjxIB8obv3z35ulLR-NksxUUI"],"When":"2024-2-11"},{"Name":"L N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_x0jhMpHDzeVBirF0fxLRLIiwfUa3JFQKGDkh8FZCNVbNfn8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great cafe, food was great, the owner was also there and he made sure I was happy with my order. Lovely to sit outside as well when you have nice weather.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNm8u_wc31KhMJ_Hr9AH0YwsjYjHqrC05WIrkQ"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Jessica Tong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItU6QX0bcOlgrqI_LeSS9NHl05jZRlljclPHJ5XLikbMcGIG4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee is excellent. Ambience is nice. Great service, super attentive. Just had some toast and that was delicious. Nice spot to meet a small group of friends as it’s not too noisy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brandon So","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw1N7FcfcI0GI2GxjHVyCLMkhxqGaQk7utW2nJtyQfoXBIYW0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered the iced matcha latte and all I could taste was the milk with a hint of matcha, definitely would not recommend. Also, the staff were very unfriendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFDHbR7NA2V_jdmsw9zoy-pTmxkJWNah5Drakx"],"When":"2024-5-30"},{"Name":"Abby Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIBPLsZWd5YIOL3Ja9odSgxm8lfQcCNwD9oUlkq5Z_gUVZp1fO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great iced Matcha Latte! I asked for mine with honey for a little sweetness (personal preference) and it was lovely! So glad I have found a good matcha latte source right beside my office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5C3asbc9W8mDXFhlUangXMSk2bOw3facHE4JwixLd933Zfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pastry was nice but would have been better if they warmed it up. Coffee was good. Asked the staff where each coffee goes but put both of the on the table a bit further away from us","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMJyWXCeKS9XbZfx_ZKC90TV84BZR-Zqux2zhP"],"When":"2023-6-29"},{"Name":"Lauren Gatt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYnV55AR9ysgskwdfMY2lLkdYyfkmTVKYZWwKGRZYa6JtRuvU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great coffee and set up - great service as well. Will come back regularly!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsnWzirx9wdQuUH7oMT89wxXBZBBgK2r1Nh1i4"],"When":"2024-4-15"},{"Name":"Asianfoodninja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVACaWn4afWhpVGICjYUweIz1CVZYHvgtMC5LkzKBKE9QCe_FOYOw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Haven't visited for a while and it seems the congee was still on the menu, so I had to order it.

Brings back good memories since it was really good back then. Food and service were good and staff were friendly.

Sat outside since it was a nice day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8912z4uRLm8cgE4jc2imacFpdvEjzjQwRZnJM"],"When":"2022-4-29"}]

[{"Name":"Vicky Rastelli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVppHQUsAIb5TGfyj49n3776z45PDo_5l2bIRh6h9MBOpjGGxOB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the poke bowl, and it was delicious, filling, tasty, light, well balanced, and healthy. Strawberry drink was recommended and super refreshing! It was a beautiful day, so i sat outside. Service was kind, a really nice experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbfNlgdAZe6QoRh0xMwFCytrJ7hvXswdm3qmZi"],"When":"2024-4-15"},{"Name":"Niki Vasiliadis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIoDzqnYnWE4Q0nBG7xeqB_obRNLdRAd3cXUgXZXHFnHacEQMF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Excellent almond milk latte. Creamy texture and perfect temp. The berry fruit juice and passion fruit soda are freshening. The blueberry and cottage cheese muffin was weird, not sure if those flavours go together.
Service is quiet and efficient but not warm or friendly. It’s busy and the staff get on with their jobs.
Compact in side, there is seating inside and outside, probably best for groups of 2-3 max.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO-xQ3yrudlBFV6T6F5OKa-kL0_RM4ACpQEm4-"],"When":"2023-10-13"},{"Name":"Michelle Markuse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkuKMDK8CjUMLvTInTxvw0HZYoZUcBrXM9WGr6FzwTBqgJP_pIDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This little coffee shop is always packed and buzzing with a good  crowd and serving great Coffee cakes and sandwiches. lots of friendly staff means that takeaway coffee is quick and efficient.🥰","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtvv7L7n-1sgmTDLGFvIZWMwbiWtaSghCr5BH6"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Good Guy Zed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJn4NTTRS-ByO66w_yRhZUlVhxHBTqX4u11t2lXLr_r5rqlCw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious coffee. Space is small but well designed and although I couldn't get a seat the coffee is beautifully well rounded and everything I wanted. Decaf is my order and hard to master but was pleasantly surprised. Didn't pay too much attention to the price but whatever I paid it was worth it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nutt Choksirikulchai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlUZ2nKlu81HIGhSdhCB7C4CSjUx9wo-scM-s8ssHkjB6dkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had coffee latte, a decent one. The atmosphere is great, love the decorations and vibes. Lots of people during lunch, but seating is still enough.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2gwGrLUps9L84dGsVmesqamDKEVc9By3-8278"],"When":"2023-11-13"},{"Name":"Emma F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWL7sVdd7sIR1E49DOetDESLKMS5KBwhCunarVIUyHc-05KVFFn3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Salad bowls here have gone down hill in the year since I've visited, see if you can guess which photos were more recent! Mine was soggy and the avocado was old. But they do have an interesting mixture of ingredients. Nice staff, cute tables and cutlery.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW3wKAXlNsj0zvuLTAg02qo7c2BSswWSgpnu__"],"When":"2020-11-25"},{"Name":"Zhuo Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9toXYu3MgCAfsNYcVrWCbF5-ReG4oIQdy_khnpNn1zisSQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favorite breakfast and coffee spot in Sydney so far!
Their flat white and Mocha are both delicious , especially the mocha, very good balance between espresso and chocolate, not too sweet and high quality!

The avo smash is delicious too! I love how much thoughts the chef put into the dish. They put the macerated lemon and sesame seeds into the dish which are very interesting. The poached egg are perfectly made. Great job!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8g0Yz03ovMT65esNbhBxg5XbOL-NUu8Ab3XBK"],"When":"2022-7-20"},{"Name":"Stella C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD62LpKWwtXT4DMSwRpuG0xd9RbC375dXOaF_fMT8DaJNHULPl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stopped at Regiment twice this week, I love their bagels! Wagyu & Chicken Avocado bagels are absolutely delicious!😚","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYItSmJmZWTjE8YPFsvVY-Hz1R4pFhqiMcqVUu"],"When":"2023-8-29"}]

[{"Name":"Hammad Qaisar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsjXsQAf3B3XZ1ZLGltZN6MKvJWDlRlOj2sCoWU1JPntYyUnOp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5/5 stars! Joe's Black is a must-visit for coffee lovers! The breakfast and lunch options are delicious, and the classic retro vibe is a great bonus. But what really sets this place apart is the owner, Alan - he's friendly, welcoming, and makes the experience even better. Highly recommend stopping by and saying hi!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6_Y0PmdH4A6zxhxC6NW9LvpaXANXXlJpY7sjf"],"When":"2024-5-31"},{"Name":"MB H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgQkMEHciFqNWppFJ2C222Ua5vSH9Go0UhDsffXUveUJOKImj_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A chill neighborhood cafe. Good for brunch and breakfast. Coffee is decent.

Will come back ? YES

Pros :
- Quick and easy. Fast service.
- Food and coffee taste decent. Cant be enjoyed by various taste palatte.

Cons :
- It’s crammy inside and tends to be dark.
- Get packed during peak hour for takeaways, hence dining in flow get disturbed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7PB0zY010oA8Q9WOqSIIfvxV3UX8Dmi9b5h5_"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Wendy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCk3r6e2dD0g_kmCzU69iVsSPvHf_JAxCEblv0_urE-V0_mQo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent coffee and great food. We really enjoyed breakfast at Joe Black Cafe the other weekend. The staff are friendly and the prices are reasonable. We look forward to coming back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh6yfUTb30HcPq6Mid4Y4MA9rDWrBPDBr0ebwQ"],"When":"2024-4-26"},{"Name":"E Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLP_KLgNO1BP43fkheMr_kGZ0bR2vCaGL8eSQyeZVRRa8QhPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend this place. We ordered long black coffee, bircher muesli and sourdough toast with poached eggs and grilled tomato.
Everything was delicious.

Coffee was great (none of the disgusting astringent and bland taste you get from some other cafes).

Bircher muesli was fantastic. Portion size was massive and more importantly it had so much flavour and tons of fruit. Highly recommend this dish.

Toast tasted great and eggs were cooked to perfection.

Couldn't fault anything.

The owner was very cheerful and active, which was good to see.

Sorry about the rude customer who got all weird and upset when you asked him to move the pram so we could leave.

If we come to Sydney again, we will definitely be coming back for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoXWjIU9genxgD6XOBVFfJT2XfZgueQCUstRdD"],"When":"2024-2-9"},{"Name":"Abbey Moloney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwcxDrpTXwT_fycFzwJ2DbaL0-K-LToTG16to4iFCJM-ZQmg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Don’t usually leave reviews but the service from (who I am assuming is the owner) was so nice. He was so friendly and lovely. Complimented my tattoos which put a big smile on my face! Had the jasmine tea which was with a twist. Was delicious. Then for breakfast I had sourdough, avo and smoked salmon which was a great portion size and value for money. Would recommend to anyone in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOag2U9zZZxnHyShCKju-z0TQvTrI7hQYoBVakv"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Julia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtO2ExWwZzZXptv8cKX4wef9dtMUVFeL_PHPObZsW-v34hM8Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service, good location, loved the atmosphere in the cafe. Came here three times for breakfast, every time super good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPY-yikixQV06N8nh__zZZFjIQ1G2LVkZ0TfQPH"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Matt Gleason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBo8oQP71y0fJi0oKAKaehv1cLtHzRmPnuJLVHHa3ncd7LJCUs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you Alan and Team! Visiting Sydney, jet-lagged, waking up way too early and we needed a place to eat breakfast. Joe Black’s was open so we gave it a shot. It was awesome! The bolognese breakfast was delicious and the cappuccinos were great. The Barista brings next-level froth artistry!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_fOruMzlMaKPRi_3VOzztk0Zla_GGvc_5nkjE"],"When":"2024-2-6"},{"Name":"SH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsxQh52GIj3m_yRikJ3jBYBz7VdGsEt76T8HOkQfSpc7DXZdSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have no idea why I never came before; 4.6 stars on Google reviews (out of >600 reviews) is a great score. We were not disappointed. The owner was very friendly, the staff great, and the food was great, too. I like the atmosphere with all these plants. I will be back for sure. It will probably become one of my regular cafe for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwKos2Ii_wbPTHw7Mz_045IbqPeHs6nsFpeYTr"],"When":"2023-10-7"}]
