[{"Name":"L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWymTteCdJuxTCPLG7fhbz1M1UEVhZ0jvFHjobpxvze9wx_lotw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great food and brunch place to chill at. Food was delicious but a little pricy, but that’s every brunch place. There were quite a few people there as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhGH-xcPtMowA6cOyjxvTnCFTqrK42ogrBhXDw"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Nicholas Beachen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzYhpn1ql3pnyqY7BTCe1Sjcdzk79akqj159g7FNmD_LwnLhJw-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Had the bacon samdwhich.

Asked for rocket removed and replaced with baby spinach and was charged extra for it.

Sandwhich was horrible tasting. I hardly ate it. Service staff didn't ask about it when taking it away.

It was toasted and rock hard. Sorry I didn't get a picture of it.

Coffee was ok, but no batch brew is sad.

Spent $40

Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuJWOyEvcGUhho_H5AAsspP1Iu82zv-78xBn6a"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"Nasrin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjf0SnXJBAWXy19Y1slpoxLRUDeq4gJ05uRRNvuzkvHAQCopa2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For a brunch that feels like a warm hug, head to Mister Sunshine's with cozy vibes and delicious dishes served with a smile, it's the perfect spot to start your day right. From fluffy French toast to mouthwatering omelts,  every bite is a tast of happiness.
Stop by there and treat yourself to a frindly brunch experience and you won't forget!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxZ0EZR0V2ipllTOISsonPUv8ehXSzXzcP-k85"],"When":"2024-2-24"},{"Name":"Bear and Dad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVba8fKnEaBIOygWQfKpJVxFskG-W2W7-tD4GbH3G8Tg4lJ_9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A completely unexpected hidden treasure.  Despite all of the high-end reviews of Mr. Sunshine and being included on lists of “Places to eat”.  We stumbled upon this café, as the highest rated breakfast restaurant in the area.  We were not sure driving over to it as it is in an industrial, in a tucked away area.  But once we got there, boy were we surprised at what we found.

We found a very cozy, welcoming fun atmosphere.  If you go here, you will know what we mean.  Plenty of seating outside in a covered, enclosed area.  If you are chilly out there, they even have homemade blankets you can pull over your shoulders.  Inside, we felt like we were at home, but if our home was retro.  It was such a comfortable spot to be in.  It had a retro feel, a lot of buzz, with music playing on a record player.  Just a joy to see.

Add, on to that no matter how busy they are (which has been both times we have been there), they are all very attentive, and give amazing service.  We never make reservations, but they have always quickly found ways to accommodate us.

Now the food takes this spot to a whole new level.  The flavours mix in what you would expect with a traditional brunch, but they add in the amazing flavours of areas like the middle east.  Every dish is executed very well, which would seem surprising based on how busy the kitchen it, but it has been consistently great. We would recommend the shakshuka eggs, the french toast and “El Capitan” breakfast.

Overall, high recommendations for Mr. Sunshine.  We can confidently say they will not disappoint but will surprise you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFjg4an2SWfEuXesO-cwKzVcNZiKCqRR8p6I6I"],"When":"2023-11-25"},{"Name":"Daryl Gilbert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdZkV-O369rhNr_BqpUfg9TS9FuYJOoKgzhQuxKsjuWdYL6kdx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just like Nonna's house. Food is consistently delicious!
Today's meals were the Divorced Benny (amazing) and the ceaser salad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUsgWG2hQpH_bPg5VhUPjhz2khwWmU4OxPhzgE"],"When":"2024-2-26"},{"Name":"majosanchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxBxBs86tfR03P9gdhXr6H2AsK5nM7ENYA6tAq0sO1usmFPDccsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"1. Food was delicious but the hot chocolate was not quite good.

2.the atmosphere is pet friendly and kids friendly

3. But We received a service from a xenophobic and racist staff because she treated differently between our and the others tables.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6r1LfTI8KZ9uupwl14UVnsKdMyyIGDoBpribA"],"When":"2023-12-10"},{"Name":"Dianne Preece","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmL9QfD-OqBhLO3EVUrch2gLPbBvtN6HN39vKU-Gn6uoP3sA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited Mister Sunshine's for brunch last Sunday for the first time and I'm always very happy when I struggle to choose something because the menu options are so good. Eventually I chose the House Cured Salmon which was really good although a small criticism is it needed two eggs rather than one to sauce the salmon so next time I'll order an extra poached egg. Good coffee and prompt service so I'll definitely go back again because it's a great location with easy parking, lovely atmosphere and pleasant staff. Sorry, I didn't take a photo but trust me it was good.

My next visit might be lunch as again, many excellent options.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Suraiya Onnesha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxtzCOt4igFkk1YA2crgBTHw8pn09CA2wD1zSg1lVrZt0DzNS2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food, nice antique interior, needs better ventilation, though. Could smell everything that was being cooked, which affected our appetite. Love all the plants and decor  🪴","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPaIDnjLKIV5XScQ6GhMqJgaZRdtWmJRqoOU4or"],"When":"2023-7-23"}]

[{"Name":"J K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfBNfGJqbUNuHkARP8PKRbVW5OYuJjrkF1xvOzXLdB_0Mh_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great cafe with yummy food and service! I ordered the crab fritters. It was delicious and fluffy and a huge serve of salad that was so refreshing! The coffee was excellent! The service was great. They kept checking on what I needed or how the food was.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYjlTPOnNRR0rKwI_rnfj_wap2zJW5RMj3xbq6"],"When":"2024-3-6"},{"Name":"Rebecca Kmit","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhv1PvK0j9PVzTJBqkxo45HCzzmoVx6v5quZ1mcD99d63zyVqM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A wonderful cafe on the less busy side of the city. Retro style. Great staff and service. Food and beverage always super speedy and great quality. Have been a few times with friends. Coffee art is exceptional! Well worth the visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSQk2Pf4qouWLDx88e_bEc0q_W0ttYbnP6pfg8"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Wendy Luu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgPTIn1KOx9O4Y4uEi62IGmnHar4z_cPqTFCzA9TAMLvGhZJ3y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Bonus points for the consistency in coffee making.
Standard brunch options. Surcharges will be applied on public holiday and weekends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6OSQB8yvW-QRsEaiVzG1mngzXX3y8-c5LAX8E"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"Nick Falkner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5LeJWJxy0YasZecfb-SYoZoJivtAyQLkGiQQvjH4QfNgrPBtR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a moment in town and wanted a quick lunch so headed back to Kingdom. Coffee was excellent, as always, and the new crab fritters are the perfect combination for a hot day: great cooling salad with perfectly cooked and tasty crab fritters. Really nice plate of food for lunch! Staff were wonderful, as usual!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEeFwgpVzbwWGkqwvoQODLCpoCAb8gIrpMvXhw"],"When":"2024-1-12"},{"Name":"Aneeka Macdonald","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpksKznpYPMcmqbffVWdK-UcV4IovHusZdS95aMYEXZ8rq-1U=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely place for a coffee, the staff interacted well with our toddler who was a huge fan of the babychinos. The latte art was also so cute I didn’t want to drink it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU5Zvq_EWS9pEa18q0PBBucoW0PTFoocBX9YW5"],"When":"2024-4-19"},{"Name":"Adelaide Cafes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVT78P6jBghWCweVysn06-E9tOhDhVC93bnIVSiZHXLuIM2v3I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Coffee is very impressive! Right temperature and taste special! Festive latte art is so cute. But food is a bit over priced. 2 pieces of Waffles with syrup and cheese alone is 24.9 on the menu and 5 dollar extra for the fruits. The waffle in the picture cost 32.9 on Sunday which is the most expensive one I ever had in Adelaide. Will definitely be back for coffee though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsIy7eRHBdP9YtKFkbE3h4CUsjlcHiSoEIQdzg"],"When":"2023-12-10"},{"Name":"Daryl Gilbert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdZkV-O369rhNr_BqpUfg9TS9FuYJOoKgzhQuxKsjuWdYL6kdx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Consistently 5 stars. The food is always delicious. I've been coming here for many years and the coffee is always great, the eggs Benny is top tier, and I've never had a meal that I've thought was less than amazing.
Tried the fish tacos today - fresh and delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-9NkUWlLvLSDCm4DeEcfs_6XOYPiGCFB0QHql"],"When":"2024-1-9"},{"Name":"Avril Atkeg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxcUC0CxQGBQ5EPL8ymFnGPPs5KlQwo6g0wo3Bd2I8hZ8iDbME=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Neat cosy cafe tucked in a quiet neighbourhood, making it an excellent place to hang out with friends or just dine solo. Service is fast and friendly. Dining can be indoors or alfresco.

Brunches are varied, mostly with sourdough toasts. Enjoyed the different egg brunches, with generous toppings of salmon or bacon or other options. Good presentation of food! Returned to try a lunch option, Ocean trout in potatoes. It was flavourful and melts in the mouth. Salad was a tad too sour for me, which overpowered the fresh taste of the rocket leaves.

Coffee aroma is awesome! Perks you right up and the latte art is superb (see the dragon!). Chai latte is no longer as good, in fact tasted more dilute this time. Dessert disappointment is the caramel cake slice, which had a hard slab of chocolate on top. Could be better if it was easier to slice through. Came back again to try the fresh lime tart, which was average. Tart casing wasn't crumbly nor light, quite hard to cut through with the fork. Had to downgrade rating from 5 to 4 stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTlnUelycrbVAYac-kWE9hC3ISLetEYjtN4jW1"],"When":"2024-3-19"}]

Had the Veggie breakfast which was delicious. Although for $28 it would have be great to have two pieces of toast. Banana smoothie had all the right combination of ingredients and refreshing. Coffee was ok, will get a stronger one next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPx7SfEOhmlHi2ALjQYcOlE9C6uPXyBFUZ1Lkvz"],"When":"2024-1-13"},{"Name":"Nelly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhSWPVQrBMYfnhFhbc17HutZofZr02nPwXivZnbswy8YIM5JZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really nice cafe with outdoor seating.\nGreat coffee, smoothies and juices.\nA good menu and overall the food was quite tasty. We had the French toast, fritters, pancakes and mushroom dish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcAmPtzzvxW_r7OVTzQzLA_DzlSYaRv3BxSHMR"],"When":"2023-12-22"},{"Name":"Naomi Lambert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLk-OH6MFR8NSXgvtMMm8KJTGzgE7PXnKq1mgdaptYH3Rtbc-yK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Outstanding corner cafe on Hutt Street! The service is exceptional, the omelette is incredible, and the fresh juices are a definite favorite. The ambience is spot on, making it perfect for a Saturday morning hangout. Bonus points for happily providing water for a thirsty little puppy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOy7faoK9J2JfFfrd895DwfMSboMacUOl7E5qQi"],"When":"2023-12-28"},{"Name":"Krystal Carr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMe3EhGHBHJTLHRU0Y_X3dTQkhQSEp4MU_fJCNdUCH4i1qMg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ate in for breakfast and was not disappointed. Staff were friendly, coffee was great and the sweet corn fritters were great. The “poached” egg was the best I’ve eaten as I normally steer away from poached as they are water drenched and I prefer my eggs well done. The Asian salad was a nice fresh addition and it was nice to have a non bread option for breakfast which wasn’t fruit, yoghurt or Muesli.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOryz6G6n9R6k15HBfcmbYUbhZGNd5HoOjtvzD7"],"When":"2023-7-4"},{"Name":"Francisca Mallea Lillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUihMmqtWBzZZ_itqBgtil_VCMUI5SSYnZqdCNwSMVyG9DK9AKr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice food, big plates and many vegan options!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgG2UV-bmx2L9Aq6sqOk_mqoYGUZoRbjwyDThc"],"When":"2024-5-17"},{"Name":"Liisa Grace Baun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzdXadkeTEUTS7Dmz70-dDFP-GyPkjrACFK9xnF_Jq9dmazLJM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Busy cafe in good location. Decent variety of food. I had a breakfast meal which was quite nice. Indoor and outdoor seating available. Parking is not so easy. I had to park at the end of the side street that this cafe is on. One person in our group has a disability so I dropped that person out the front first. By the time I found a park and walked there, my food was no longer warm. This is no fault of the cafe owners but something that patrons could be aware of.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4A8sI0iCfUX6O89s-4lPFJFAahcmjxmKwCocm"],"When":"2023-3-21"},{"Name":"Julie B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiuUpzq7EXWuu-Dt7f55uFKNhktspZJvjjrV4buyHHnn9pmQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee is great here and very quickly delivered to the table. We’ve been coming here for years and are never disappointed with the quality of the food. Service is great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCLKb80OT1LQSLY5-1FlDSgYktF4FwgFdMsk9G"],"When":"2023-11-12"},{"Name":"therezeegoes_","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUp3vKBJXzcWnIqfYoxX49xOU_hbi5R2rKnLgjIBp2_BCN8r-k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely cafe with yummy food, the staff were very friendly","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJEJXRxyXP63dAb0H0PbXPojSAFzRX0fj5zPlH"],"When":"2023-12-12"}]

Too bad everything on the strip is closed by 3pm!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM7kVJwxlugLinmrQuWCCd8IucGmfA-VAEEUDE"],"When":"2024-3-1"},{"Name":"Manmeet Chhabra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJccKWGfbKh-GT1Vebx6rBpxhQlZCChJwA4fvXj1UgFjOi9omh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is an amazing place to have your meals. I usually go here for my Saturday breakfasts and end up spending 2 hours, enjoying the atmosphere and the service.
The hosts are awesome,making you comfortable straight away and showing real interest to chat with you.
The food is delicious and well presented.
Conveniently located near a children's park, with ample parking spaces around.
Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2YDUHk6oVD5E9Lk2rodBMFs1QrC5PtdENXpjU"],"When":"2022-5-21"},{"Name":"Edward Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0h7YwVTOIabOBDV9jR0l7jhpD30mbDIc6T3Uw0Q9iHtCnYxk5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome place surrounded by a lot of coffee shops and bakery shops. The food is good but the portion is small, and the drink is lovely and tasty. The atmosphere is good and better for a group of 4 maximum. Don’t need to make a reservation, you just need to walk in. Highly recommended for everyone to come to this area and enjoy the breakfast or brunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSWxq7IZ2qLmOGxhYvrrrBESfmDmvtqIUazgTM"],"When":"2023-7-23"},{"Name":"Travelling Mama","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-lhEYwT8LEPVsgpjXykIwnbdFevtfxnJS046CAbL_4mqLrjwEvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We found this place nice with a cosy atmosphere and great for catch ups!!

There's a friendly staff and a wonderful, fast service too. The food was full of flavour and with great choices...great portions and worth the price...just amazing!!

Have been there before and will be going back again especially for their coffee!! Definitely recommend them for everything!! 👍💯☕️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Xavier Allen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiwlHm4BhKiUr_ktdlEaxmLUh7SYmGpHqexxlPRAH_3oy3KfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Service, workers, food, location, everything is very good with the cafe. Prices are very affordable aswell. The owner is so nice, always working hard and up for a chat. Love living over the road from it","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cixi Y.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDDAdtyfUHGWjcBcHByoNBPycFTNcmvJW1H188h4Eb-_TLQHGrHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friendly staff plus really good and very filling food!

Flat white and mocha were both bomb!!! 👌No bitter taste at all 👏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHkMi0ejGm05ulXuKPoPRAUinCBeXQ575WZuSz"],"When":"2021-12-21"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Nico Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgVV0g34nwB62VOpZR7LbiPr8kLDh0viMv2m1921EMhAtqW9ly=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Very neat space and fairly functional; seating outside for a social get away, bar/bench seating if you’re flying solo and several tables for groups of 2-6 if you’re eating in.
Great staff and good coffee, long black and an almond piccolo.

Didn’t have food yet great colour on the dishes being g served, atmosphere wasn’t vibrant yet with the venue being a little less than half full it is a good place to step away from the city busyness.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoymgNz9gmEgB4NrQh2oPMTfIoHDC8C6UyS1Cp"],"When":"2024-4-30"},{"Name":"Cara Gjuzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcrYnM0_7MnhofSxXgIH41dx4lUk9Nbi310ma_M4hrBBv1koue=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have had breakfast here two days in a row and have loved all the dishes we have ordered. Friendly and fast food that is presented beautifully and tastes delicious. Nice inside and outside seating options.
I highly recommend the avocado on toast, crab scramble and bone marrow bolognese. The porridge was also delicious for a lighter option.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPdgz5kV9s4s7dC12iMbByXSsSZjGjeHNeESte"],"When":"2024-6-1"},{"Name":"Pouria Aryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHfIHFttePjYY1RtIL_b_WYIsP_neJaQ4UFLZU9Pu77HN4BclI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely spot in the heart of Adelaide CBD. The coffee is great. The staff are very friendly and professional. The service was quick and efficient. Both breakfast choices were very tasty. The post egg was cooked to perfection, and the breaking burger was delicious and very balanced in terms of sweetness, richness and savoury. If you're looking after a decent breakfast or brunch, here is the place. Well done to the staff for the nice job.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDfP2AS2cEkMa577DCJO3LHQcqsJc1CSQekFn4"],"When":"2024-1-7"},{"Name":"Pip Andrews","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaTPMePUFMLNUkByhEfWO1mCPOy2kY3RvBAxC8FAHeE5iHmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was tasty and filling, and value for money coffee was on point, refreshing to have sparkling water served rather than still and NOT have to pay for it. Service was a bit hit and miss.  Went here 2 days in a row and both days service let it down.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIMBi5avzMcjCEkZfMxGZVHR7SbYuXnQeH37vH"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"JONATHAN POTTER","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeffymtKS6bisRBefmIMm-iwJVdIGOTk6Tqz9gYRlEur8tx9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good coffee (maybe a bit too milky on the flat white).  And nice food.  Buzzy ambience and nicely away from the traffic.  I nearly knocked a star off as they forgot our food - which is a serious no no.  When it was eventually sorted out they refunded the coffees.  And they are friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7cdCqfTAwTeZINh-_oDO3b5tB05cAh84o-4e2"],"When":"2024-1-21"},{"Name":"Wendy Luu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgPTIn1KOx9O4Y4uEi62IGmnHar4z_cPqTFCzA9TAMLvGhZJ3y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Exchange Coffee is a delightful spot for coffee enthusiasts. They brew Market Lane coffee beans, bringing a taste of Melbourne's vibrant coffee scene to Adelaide. The café offers a modern decor that has a cosy atmosphere, making it a perfect spot to relax and enjoy a cup of coffee.

As a coffee specialty shop, Exchange Coffee delivers consistent quality. I didn't get the chance to try out their food but They do have standard brunch options.

The open kitchen concept adds a unique touch, allowing customers to witness the baristas and kitchen staff in action. However, to me this feature can be a bit of a drawback as the kitchen smells can be overpowering at times. The chance you will walk out smelling like a mobile brunch is high.

It's definitely worth a visit for any coffee lover in Adelaide.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7ptI54cr850mgUrJnumoyEop1-NJ9TJnutRwv"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Ed T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKxhkVJ5iooZE7I7Tz3DwPTwzJCSYefzdfgcnztgsgcK-oBGg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty lunch of crab scrambled, roast potatoes and Peking duck noodle salad. Coffee always a standout. Relaxed atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_rgQ-1w4BoWMe7poTC5PxHprdMqfe1fXaSpoD"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"J Cozi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJA9rt6HcNxjxX166tB3THv0gpeatv5_snarGKxIvAOaehfDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We eat here almost weekly and absolutely love this place. The food, the vibes and the coffee!

Fantastic brekkie and lunch options, consistent quality food and excellent coffee.

Great quality GF bread... a must for brunch and this place has great bread. If you are an almond milk snob... be warned no almond milk on the menu but oat milk is just as good, if not better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPI-e6tQryNQ_sz9FfSvYBITcSFkuGc4Ixlk1B8"],"When":"2023-11-24"}]

[{"Name":"anshu bhatia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-OQwSy2pzImBE2X2pAxGGMNzIty_enBp4Irw37LMvWuPRQmJ6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Vibe of this place is good. Food presentation is good but unfortunately the food isn’t that great. It’s more like a ready made kind of a place. They were serving food real quick n most of the items of your meal would be from Costco or other places. Meaning they don’t make things in house. For the price they are charging it’s not worth it. I don’t know why it still has good reviews. Also 18$ burger with nothing with it and not much inside wasn’t worth it at all. Coffee was fine though. More like a touristy place. Don’t think locals visit it much.!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOI6YVbmQcYWs_GVBFEUbQvqtNK8Tvmg60FPLdL"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"Jaimin Patel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjjMp6hClG0hpQDVfyyRipE3kGULWBTKjauGYmFpF8uPMqO7Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My regular Mocha coffee at UR Caffe is rich and perfectly brewed, making mornings delightful. I would like to recommend to all Muesli Breakfast you will love it. Friendly staff and very quick service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOynwCjD0HORSavVuZKYU3RxfsBAXJoIT6HABFX"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Sarah Norris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3oiZd2aA42gkKsJF3B_3mhB2E0oVOLcM1O6R9A-QuK8idUzvC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic service! Very friendly, excellent coffee! I don’t finish my breakfast but that’s a me problem because the food was delicious!! Hubby smashed his burger and bowl of coffee though and hopefully made up for it! Lol","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtbd0LQydD3sJ4mgOJlHXrBu-1AX6VHrmtpvHp"],"When":"2024-2-23"},{"Name":"Joy Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9dPaviltmg4VDs_aVJYGkyUNEW0AAYoXtP2--PZ1iQ9J9uwA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Did not expect much from this place when we randomly walked in but it’s one of the best brunch I’ve ever had

Staff were really lovely, the place itself is a bit small and noisy but great choice in food. I really enjoyed my plate of dish which I recommend. I don’t remember the dish name anymore but this salmon was so refreshing and good! The smoothie was also nice

Parking is okay, street parking available
I recommend to check this place out","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlrN0MS1Qlg7w_U-OH5US5eFwGKa_lYv1N52Bz"],"When":"2023-7-8"},{"Name":"Chenyu Jia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSHrY-9Zf_Vzqk9qCVeQMop7y2RkFI6aqAtwEksgf0LtPkCPQG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee, not bad! I tried the Thai coffee with condensed milk. It’s kind of like Vietnam coffee but sweeter.

Burger, yum! The bun is fluffy and delicious!

Waffle, avoid at all costs. 🥲 it looks great and the ice cream is delicious, but the waffle itself tastes exactly like the Costco frozen one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHcK3CJs3OwRoGqbXQn7cWvQriRvk9lrl9EXYW"],"When":"2024-1-16"},{"Name":"Adelaide Cafes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVT78P6jBghWCweVysn06-E9tOhDhVC93bnIVSiZHXLuIM2v3I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I order a flat white with orange peel. It tastes amazing and refreshing! You can smell a bit citrus aroma before you start to drink the coffee. And the combination is so well balanced. Love their idea. However Omelette is a bit well done and thin like well cooked fried egg, a bit different than I expected. I was expecting it would be fluffier.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjTHAkVuhzrgoEk_GO6bj5rcSMBP10Bn0ftVEE"],"When":"2024-1-5"},{"Name":"Paul Burford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6xQrIGkzgVJZqQFFZfV7GkdyZZ6qSSQUL-lUWK6aPm4HVuKREMg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice welcome on arrival, very friendly staff. Coffee and food came out pronto, nicely presented and high quality!
Easy to see why it's very busy early on a Sunday morning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqwIS7GKkqkqeHj8MZoWX6Y82eczswUJRawxub"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"Mamata Shrestha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmIjEgiijO9YyfvoXgLR8hj80Rms_9ZaHhhlxTPlPOh8DsnISn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food , yummy burger , loved the ambience, customer service at its best , best Jaffa  hot chocolate with orange peel 10/10. Enjoyed my weekend breakfast  at ur cafe","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbTnSOxZJs_iX6fNXvMWCK-lBIfPxKRgHdZ3LD"],"When":"2024-5-5"}]

[{"Name":"Liza Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSoIjG_7wb5b9V6egg3pKO9gTgGcfSc5DP4Mmm0ZZXGUDcWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Your typical and classic eggs and toast sandwiches, bugers and coffees spot. I was there a couple of times for brunch on the weekends and have enjoyed the food and bustling ambience. I tried the chai latte last weekend and it was so tasty. Will be back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP27wKi7nwtqNR7Qs56vI3JtwJV_4uCAz4GSggC"],"When":"2024-4-11"},{"Name":"Veronica Thompson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJR9c_WTIiCvpyb8fVU1wkQdkUcVijKZ1FTfQEU1LcY0w5KqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a fantastic breakfast this morning @ Zuma. I had Snag & eggs + hash browns & hubby had bacon & eggs on toast + 2 large cappuccino. Great flavours, poached eggs were perfect, quick service. Staff were very lovely & accommodating. Good price, too. We sat & enjoyed the atmosphere while we watched the buzzing market customers & traders. Will be back soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeFaAaHu5rW45RiZX6LSy3pGDvtvCSxeet7wRw"],"When":"2023-4-5"},{"Name":"Gabriel Pezzini Gazzaneo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-nxqfULaSQWaE56CuVvrFpqLBPSY00iTgi0RXhe6uo6CWxF15=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent food and service quality. Our order didn’t take more than 10 minutes to arrive, so my coffee was still hot and I was able to enjoy it with a delicious egg and bacon sandwich. My wife ordered a bacon and avocado with relish sandwich. Both of them extremely tasty, with a lot ( a lot) of bacon which - in my opinion - is always welcoming. I know that from the pictures it looks a very simple toast, but I assure you that the flavour is worth it.
Price wise the whole order was $36 dollars. Not very cheap, not very expensive. Just a fair value.

I would definitely recommend this place and would come back more times to try other things from their menu","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgNViXNWg2gasfyysKs5ij1wwBmg1i59Z3RQop"],"When":"2023-1-21"},{"Name":"Ares RS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcsGOAWZMv6GZmwv1w5HYzQWyg5Gy4wtDY_DMT-LKgDsschsiH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Zuma Coffee is a local gem, renowned for its exceptional coffee. Popular among locals, it offers rich flavors and a cozy ambiance. For coffee enthusiasts seeking quality brews, Zuma Coffee is a must-visit spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoTG3uqqKmZnv4Ne2Wk9-hv42qmS0RyzTy9rrG"],"When":"2023-12-29"},{"Name":"Nick B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVqAQ8J8U4lgzZ-aRpdsoO_y6a0a4jzprCMZDSneFxg93D2Mg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible experience - went there with my wife and my elderly mother. While trying to find a table, staff were very unhelpful. After sitting down and receiving the food, it was obvious the food and service was terrible. Everything turned up looking bland. I had the roast chicken sandwich that virtually had no chicken on it and was overtoasted (stale bread to start with). My mother had a toasted cheese sandwich which was bland, virtually no cheese and ham, definitely not fresh. My wife had the smoked salmon which was also poor. I complained to the manager who was a bald headed old guy. He was incredibly grumpy and basically told us bad luck, that's what it is - no refund or replacement. Worst customer service I ever had. The manager needs to learn to listen to his customers and not to argue with them. Do not go there, it's total rubbish.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andres Venegas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHvmCh8dwhC3SS85bhcO7RL4Vd-KGd7YfcwLNVvyY8HVmeIZ_Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The family and I visited Adelaide (first time for me) and Zuma was the first spot we visited for breakfast: and was so for 3 days straight! Everything about this bustling cafe was fantastic! Despite the bustling mornings, the staff worked like a well-oiled machine, always friendly, and efficiently serving consistently delicious and generous portions from an albeit medium-sized kitchen.Truly a great way to start the morning for any traveller! Definitely would recommend to anyone looking to later visit the Central Market, and definitely recommend the Bacon Eggs Benedict!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyCg433lClFp51eyP-14gUaGQxbo3TTlcsN6qo"],"When":"2023-12-30"},{"Name":"Ming Khor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzg_ZGy8zkMi0POE4dHVO_Z92lja0W_0wkk_OYQgaYf6DqrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went to this place to have lunch. Got an Aussie Burger (2 beef patties) and a cup of coffee. Burger was about 20 dollars and the coffee must have been 4.50. Coffee tasted great. The burger was good value. A lot of meat. A bit on the dry side. Otherwise this would be a 5 star review","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfNs1MmjvOUnHiE2J8euUayOH6hUYh-uj6iyS6"],"When":"2023-7-29"},{"Name":"Quinn Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMfRnkWFctomN5x_CLYmiA_UYtTJ1gSA3_ZBAmf4nP_RdwFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had the red thai curry. One of the bedt meals ive ever had in Aus. Massive portion of seafood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgSvUPcH-rfwWXgkhiF36KH9Np1HDrortnasIB"],"When":"2024-3-2"}]

[{"Name":"Kenny Tam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQQJaka6aKh0fD2LYbbJB1f5wQSfQihGbLgDvYYeXInrRCZ79q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I am really disappointed with Scootz Cafe. We tried the “breaky for two”. The size was gorgeous but all the food were too salty to finish. However, the young man created a beautiful latte art for the hot chocolate which  I really appreciated it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkDsb8R-iUNZ4IDYkZ4CqLor9Rchwa32QAtWek"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Angie Bastone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAGEp_4YzTKq1HxInrk5zaNrpOR1aTEMw_tJB1Yw99jgNyow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had come for a trip to Adelaide from Melbourne, we were looking for somewhere ro have breakfast and this place happened to be just around the corner from our hotel, the food was amazing, the staff were lovely and very enthusiastic and you can tell they love what they do. They all had great energy and enthusiasm and made sure we had a great time. We had two of the Scootz big brekkys and it was the best breakfast my partner and I had ever had and absolutely amazing prices. My partner and I said as we walked out that we have to come back to Adelaide and try more of their menu !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSzwv_wmZFV1O8zXBxtKPfdWinOqwCEFnET3Ad"],"When":"2024-2-16"},{"Name":"Janeece Walmsley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvd00CSO7uWU0vPEBz5xYn3zDxOFphqcrixx4KSKW9tNG5HoVE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had the opportunity to stumble on this amazing cafe on Monday morning.

You know I may get emotional when my heart strings are pulled ♥️ and this happened here seeing this gorgeous family all supporting each other in their family business.

However the coffee was great as was our breakfast too 👍😘👍😘👍

So when in next in town please check it out!!

They do lunch too - yiros and pizza 🍕 etc
Definately  going back ✔️👍❤️

#supportfamilyowned #supportfamilyownedbusiness #skootzcafeadelaide","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM95RrcmNUSOq1IUYxloJnv5OI0duayhlPRl0Eu"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Toyah Meekel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxfNwprGFmfwefy-pJDhfgFf6gZYFMKL8bFCmElZL9lKUpABU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I needed a quick wholesome lunch nearby and stumbled past Scootz - great options for vegetarian/vegan. The boys were super welcoming and helped make me an epic fresh juice! Falafel salad was huge! Packed with ingredients and a great dollop of hummus and dressing - delicious! Everyone who came in was made to feel welcome and the atmosphere was great - thanks again team!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPA5xO8WJKBHpOp41RSKttvzqrs_BxPMDRKVKfb"],"When":"2023-11-9"},{"Name":"Kelly Hunter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRZDo2kiFXI2VeM0P5nQI-DlvLCA4Ry1bz5gnX3u8qZd4RZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Open on the public holiday and we had amazing, friendly service. Very accommodating. Delicious food! Owned by lovely people who took the time to talk with my family. Quick service! Will definitely be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kaylee Western","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrr0GFTV_ByYpc4CYqxqtwJth_9GqtA0ng-IQj-eSZrMqp0w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing breakfast for two this morning. Everything was extremely tasty and presented beautifully. The staff were absolutely lovely and ensured us that there is plenty of gluten free options which we needed :) 10/10 recommend.
Pic attached of gluten free version of the breakfast for two","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9h2VDWJbC11Dm41c144weFzuujW_qS6V8UhrT"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"Derek Henderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiQ7CRIxsYeYWCtAYNJi38cUg_j7-VWJIQYcFwoTJiXj3crfY-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My recent visit to Scootz Cafe on Pultney Street in Adelaide, South Australia, was nothing short of a culinary revelation. Not only did I experience exceptional service from the friendly staff, but I also had the pleasure of savoring the outstanding 'Burger with the Lot.'

Let's talk about the star of the show - the 'Burger with the Lot.' This burger is an absolute triumph of flavors and textures. From the very first bite, it was evident that Scootz Cafe takes its burger game seriously:

Freshness and Generosity: The burger was a masterpiece of freshness and generosity. Piled high with an abundance of fresh, crisp vegetables, it was a sight to behold. Each bite was a delightful medley of textures and tastes, making it an absolute joy to devour.
Perfectly Cooked Patty: The burger patty itself was a work of art. Cooked to perfection, it was juicy, flavorful, and boasted a satisfying char. It was clear that Scootz Cafe's attention to detail extended to every component of this burger.
Flavor Explosion: What sets this burger apart is the perfect balance of flavors. The combination of cheese, sauces, and the medley of toppings created a harmonious explosion of taste. It was a symphony for the taste buds, and I savored every bite.
Visually Stunning: Not only did the 'Burger with the Lot' taste incredible, but it was also a visual feast. The presentation was impeccable, showcasing the care and craftsmanship that goes into each dish at Scootz Cafe.
Now, let's circle back to the friendly staff. Their warm welcome, attentiveness, and genuine enthusiasm for their food and customers enhanced the overall dining experience. They made sure that my visit was not just about great food but also about creating lasting memories.

In summary, Scootz Cafe's 'Burger with the Lot' is a culinary masterpiece that deserves all the accolades it receives. If you're a burger connoisseur or simply looking for a memorable dining experience in Adelaide, this burger should be at the top of your list. Coupled with the exceptional service from the friendly staff, a visit to Scootz Cafe is an absolute must. I can't wait to return for another taste of this burger and the warm hospitality that makes Scootz Cafe truly exceptional!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOccruzrew34Uip9Nfg18gabdJnWgnUNqfgYHTp"],"When":"2023-9-28"},{"Name":"rosslyn peacock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-29Adlcl1bXNkbF6KHY2gvAtVHz7qtEFGePKZtiEmTE8zQg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had coffee and a brownie but it was good.  Some other folk had a breakfast and it looked amazing.  Sitting outside enjoying may coffee and watching the world pass by.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The fresh donuts get a mention too - yum!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORsRA0M1Wzs_VL0QB7GwDI40VTj870cMsP6V9x"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Isla lsla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ2IYbeYKRIQbkpAau6NmVMrR5121E5Scbz4QNt9i4PhGlpbY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We order Baked Eggs Claypot and Fried Chicken&Egg Waffle. The food is generous and well presented. The Staff are very friendly. If you're in the city for the day, highly recommend this place! We will come back again!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_n54_mXWzlPO-xL9Kio6fLqcrBSZjXjrkIDvA"],"When":"2024-5-28"},{"Name":"Bill Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJohPs7I3SValJwNmR5Wbkr4pwErvIhQUBSQ3DxzyHDgCeKYkZxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This delightful coffee shop sits amongst residential and commercial buildings in leafy Gilbert Street in the South West corner of Adelaide City. We came for a simple coffee break and so glad we came here.
The service is friendly and welcoming, and the coffee is excellent (so impressed we even purchased beans to take home).
They offer a tempting menu and an array of pastries to enjoy. Just for a quick visit we couldn't resist the strawberry pastry.
Tables inside and outdoor or just takeaway.

We'll be back for sure","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUhFPL4ycePRDHUpBO0pvTl2dZ_T07ZsH1byWs"],"When":"2024-3-13"},{"Name":"Belle F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9q9Udpyh35oBYSLhsEwXgkTtkZ9a51b2jsG6fQ-AJefAMJw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely love having breaky here. The coffee  & matcha latte is perfect everytime. The souffle pancakes are fluffy & jiggly & hit the spot everytime! The fish baos are a must try & love the cauliflower baos & baked eggs are great vegetarian options!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2_huxBgwAUclTeqX3Aw3RgcTgIo43SpEZb8d8"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Dany Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBgT52G1XJIiqnhBU_D796Ny0oNBEiki77SOEQbW09QMvoftpj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm glad to see a brunch spot offering more creative options. The staffs were friendly and provided attentive service.
However, cleanliness was a bit lacking, as the tables emitted the smell of dirty rags.
We ordered the fried chicken sandwich and Japanese soufflé. While they were subtle in flavor, perhaps my expectations were too high, as overall they tasted average. The soufflé had a rich eggy taste but lacked lightness and air-like texture. After finishing, the owner actually asked us, "How was it? Does it taste the same like the soufflé in Tokyo?" I was speechless for a moment; if he hadn't asked, I would have thought the soufflé I had was just still acceptable. By the way, I would recommend changing the ice cream used for the Affogato; the vanilla flavor tasted artificial.
The two of us spent 70 dollars, a price that already higher than brunch restaurants in Sydney and Melbourne.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2099pFFBDVshuSaLNVZ6Hefk3kmZQ5tjDm_vE"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Wilson Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5AJs-Am1JmD5MxtVBzB1BaQHojQIEq78vDveL57yKgCU-quH0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had lunch on a Sunday while the cafe was full we didn’t have to wait that long to get a table.

Service was fantastic, food portions very generous
Would recommend
5/5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWh6Iyty77Gpzwj0ZKe6Gv2_BLx4Yv-5w3t4ZB"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Tugba Akyildiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-ue7ct9IlX8-e--vxvWR145tnmGJAx_aWd095myWsQwd0A6l4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you're a coffee lover this is the place to pop into. The matcha french toast was delicious. Lovely staff, super friendly and service with a smile!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0NW6nrNBVWXS9QVrsUq19hIxadpulLBDXlf7l"],"When":"2024-3-19"},{"Name":"Adhi Sappareng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFRDA4enBPCcEh7eQVh09kUg2UxbkMSJqxZ-IpnZ29lOUEqoEm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I think this is one of hidden gem for brunch in Adelaide. I went there few weeks back. I was reccommended by friends and i dont regret it. They have amazing food.

The shoft chell crab with toasted croissant, OMG i will go back there for this, so tasty and yummy. The croissant so flaky.

The waffle with fried chicken, i think need more salt for the chicken, but its ok, still yummy food.

The french toast also amazing, not to sweet,

The ice macha also perfect combination with all food we ordered.

The custome service was best even only 2 staff at that time.

The place has indoor and outdoor. Definietly coming back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8-4OMxR7f_6j5OMsDoNescvpoT4M24YInRhZm"],"When":"2024-1-1"}]

[{"Name":"Betul Toprak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqCUMUr-ZNPm04Xst3339kSz9W21l5idQphbRem2YWa5FFCSs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They serve the best porridge of all times ❤️❤️❤️ and the cauliflower toastie I had might be the best toastie ever. It was a huge toastie which kept me full all day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-SAFubpizLGfkpBGnI17XHMAhmH1hskManASG"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Esther Samson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3I92SHVOar4bBEtMar0997ffqtIRp0oRvVRNRSO5c00AcKg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Discovered this gem near our hotel when visiting Adelaide for the weekend. Fab vegan options, good coffee and lovely service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMljmdlo2-zfEoj3rWBot2cUQCP4Dher9G0qVsW"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Bangyun Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1N1p1xh6gWOFdIJAsffsSzPO3M76UZy2nRvZyjktDIybErhSw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly staff and great for dog owner as there’re nice shaded outdoor sitting.
The interior of this little cafe has rusty theme decorations.
Their cauliflower toasty is very substantial.
Tangy flavour with sweet from caramelised onion with pickled radish/beetroot? at the side.
The sourdough is thick and crunchy with the nice cheeses flavour that’s melted through.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOE-VdcZam7mMhfFyYGNQW1dWKoFMvpn9oR0YdF"],"When":"2023-5-8"},{"Name":"Tim Schroeder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWWxScydyj0uyTGPEgoksUY6q0V1MKPX0q1Tkb-EUsAPbWgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 stars all the way! I'm excited to have discovered Sibling having had it recommended to me by another quality cafe in the CBD.
Sibling oozes quality from presentation, but most notably in service and food. The welcome was warm and genuine with service that you would return for.
We enjoyed lunch on one of the numerous sidewalk shaded table options. I couldn't go past the cauliflower cheese toastie that I had seen mentioned in other reviews - they were right, it was scrumptious! My partner went for the heirloom tomato and peach salad and found it to be very balanced. Both dishes were perfectly presented, bursting with flavour and thoroughly satisfying.
Coffees were very decent also.
No question that we will be back here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvyRQDSFRP3EcHsQBRAC6UUfbSPmVAVFt93cm2"],"When":"2023-3-8"},{"Name":"Leandro Zanchin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHb3Lefor77EglHQXf06W0aSK0yN-USo91fvyuhz4cHB9xTwSS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing cafe in south terrace, walking distance from the hotel I’m staying. Staff is friendly, nice and cosy atmosphere, tables inside and outside. Coffee was very good (I live in Melbourne so I’m a bit picky), the toast and muesli are just outstanding. Everything was 5 stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9hyKXU3yUDMCScHHOVaAgr7kGZnoi_y9ey58c"],"When":"2023-1-6"},{"Name":"Michelle Philp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIplOfwPyZIpDdajzPJa7bRul-fZ47Jm0auc3-6eeM3Y6FfVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The cauliflower cheese and pickle toasted sandwich is hands down the best toasted sandwich in all the land. Love the addition of sparkling table water instead of flat. Service was so great and I can't wait to come back. Thank you","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Suzanne Haynes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXB3SbKJNdnJDE_5wynDxEvt_sVE6Yu0Y_uHwYbla9rNPrnoomd3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cafe is always wonderful, with great staff, beautiful fresh food, vast menu range, priced appropriately.  We enjoyed their cauliflower toastie, rhubarb and plum porridge and beef baegal.  Great flavour combinations, generous serves and beautiful presentation.  We were able to  book ahead  via email. Bathrooms are available. Enjoy. We just keep going back and every time the food, coffee and staff and Wonderful. Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBEj1U-R6isWn0ugt6OKMUmtiJgZeaAt5DqmzO"],"When":"2024-2-4"},{"Name":"Nippon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVz3B_arIatsmAd34m_M7eIoECgJAEKju-KJzv_fO-N6hDXxhQmSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"you will enjoy the cozy vibes here. i had a good tims from the coffee and brunch, also the staff were so nice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfhrFssLXHlzen3TueW9OG0DB1jeAAxZmi0R8f"],"When":"2023-8-18"}]

[{"Name":"Katherine Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_XVAuvwgEkZ0deAnaIHlJzJOEMRDU1L9Yn2m0TTUrs-XEKDrx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place for breakfast and coffee. Scrambled eggs and bacon came with generously buttered toast.  One of the few places around here that has cold drip coffee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4hohL0PZZOBERIyAZtUWNpBpW5arEBkIxJuSi"],"When":"2024-3-8"},{"Name":"bonbon and pumpkin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXck2RPL9_O4-_34cHqqT_R0qnnRJSxzQHRK9Y7kjfEJpmgCpmr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really enjoyed my experience here - it’s definitely a meeting place . The atmosphere is quite lively , and it’s situated down a small laneway right near the Central Market .
There is indoor and outdoor seating , and they also sell some condiments and specialised food items , as well as a selection of cookbooks, and some hot chocolate powder from Morks, which is a specialised well known chocolate shop in Melbourne .
Market street cafe also have their own little bakery , which means fresh in house bread .
Their coffee of choice was D’Angelo , which is a local coffee roaster , with a deep chocolaty taste. I had an iced almond latte and enjoyed this brew .
Gluten free options are not particularly wide , but I did have a Reuben sandwich with a twist , ( with kimchi and gochujang mayo ) and was pleasantly surprised by the gluten free bread , which was thick and seeded - delicious.
